Description: Your role:As an Intelligence Analyst – System Operator (known in the Navy as Cryptologic Systems Operators) your role supports classified Government intelligence programs by analysing signal transmissions; and informing tactical and military advantage both at sea and ashore. This diverse and mentally stimulating role encompasses a range of specialist skills that support intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance activities. You’ll use sophisticated, state-of-the-art search receivers and other complex equipment to intercept, record, analyse and disseminate the intelligence of signal transmissions. Teamwork is an important part of the role. You’ll work in a close-knit team that really rely on each other. There are also many opportunities for career growth and travel; all while making a difference to the defence of Australia and her interests.As an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator, you will receive training in the  following areas:- Analytical techniques and methodical problem-solving,- Communications theory and networks,- Methods for working with intelligence information,- Preparation and presentation of intelligence briefs, and,- Provide advice to Commanders and other audiences as required. Prior experience isn’t needed. You’ll gain all the necessary skills and qualifications to become an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator as part of your training. Although, it is worth noting that successful Operators typically have a sound background in mathematics and are comfortable with the fundamentals of physics.Life in the Navy: A career in the Navy is challenging and highly rewarding, and comes with good work/life balance, competitive salary and skills for life. You can expect to feel a unique sense of accomplishment and pride from serving and protecting our country and helping to keep our vast coastlines safe.Life in the Navy is anything but mundane. You’ll enjoy varied lifestyles, rewarding careers, opportunities to travel, and excellent social and fitness facilities, free medical and dental; all in a dynamic and fulfilling working environment. Don’t worry, it’s not all life at sea—there’s more to the Navy than ships, submarines and helicopters. Some days, you might be exploring exciting new countries with your fellow crewmates. Other days, you could be stationed locally not too far from home. Salary: Upon completion of your initial military and initial employment training, you’ll enjoy a competitive starting salary package from $75,625 including service and uniform allowances. You will also receive a Maritime Allowance when serving on ships. In addition to your salary, you will receive generous superannuation, housing subsidies and free medical and dental care.Apply Now: For this role, you must be over 17 at time of enlistment, an Australian Citizen and have passed Year 10 English, Maths and Science (physics is preferable).Click the APPLY button if you think you have what it takes to become an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator and we’ll get in contact with you shortly.You can also visit the link below to view the full position description and learn more about life in the Navy.https://navy.defencejobs.gov.au/jobs/intelligence-analyst-systems-operatorThe Australian Defence Force is an equal opportunity employer. This advertisement is to ensure women are aware of the rewarding and fulfilling careers available in the Navy, Army and Air Force. Females are encouraged to apply, however all roles are open for Australian men and women to apply.

In addition, your strong Statistical analysis methodologies, including forecasting, machine learning and predictive analytics techniques will be essential to the success of this position.  Additional InformationBe ConnectedRecently acquired by Allegro Funds, a successful Australian private equity company, Global Express has an exciting future ahead and will benefit from a transformation program, underpinned by $500 million in funding to support and grow the business. It’s never been a more exciting time to join our team as we take the next step in our journey.Toll embraces and celebrates a variety of cultures. We continue to build a business that reflects the values of equality, built on the knowledge and understanding that everyone is welcome including the First Nations Peoples and those of all ages, genders and abilities.To find out more about us visit www.tollgroup.com/careersTo be considered, you must be entitled to work in the specified country and be prepared to undertake pre-employment checks including a criminal history check and medical assessment.

multiple_details: ['Melbourne', 'Northern Suburbs', 'Information & Communication Technology', 'Business/Systems Analysts', 'Full time']
Description:
Career development and growth opportunity
Not for profit with salary packaging benefits (amongst others!)
Flexible location – Melbourne, Hybrid role
 
Are you a passionate Business Intelligence Analyst that is also passionate about making a difference in your local community?
 
Calling all Business Intelligence professionals!!
An exciting opportunity has become available for an enthusiastic and talented Business Intelligence Analyst to join the team that provides the data and insights that drive the success of our business. The BI team manage the design, development, implementation, delivery and maintenance of the business insights function to support organisational performance and growth at Campbell Page.
 
The company
Campbell Page is a not-for-profit organisation delivering multi-faceted employment services for disability, youth, indigenous, labour hire and general sectors. Campbell Page also provides community services and social enterprises from more than 80 locations across four states. We’re on a mission to prevent and reduce unemployment while creating jobs in the communities we’re a part of. Campbell Page has a passion to improve the lives of people seeking employment.The role
Reporting to the Manager – Business Insights, the Senior Business Insights Analyst is responsible for delivering both daily operational requirements and strategic organisation wide initiatives. Being a small team, you will have the opportunity to really make a difference and see the positive impacts your work will have on the performance of the business and services to our customers. This is a high profile role that will allow you to develop your influence and visibility across the organisation. We believe that BI is closely aligned to the business and as such, you will have the opportunity to immerse yourself and learn about this exciting and rewarding industry.
 
This role will see you:
Collaborating with your BI and business colleagues to continually enhance the quality of data analysis and reporting
Provide proactive analysis of trends and insights into the operations and business of the company
Ensure all daily, weekly and monthly Business Insights tasks are completed on time
Working with business colleagues to design and develop new reports
Gather, extract and manipulate data from multiple databases and transform this data into ongoing reporting solutions & insights
Developing capabilities to exploit API’s from internal and external systems to extract data
Continually improve BI processes & procedures aligned with the needs of the organisation
Continuing to enhance our data management and governance processes
Continually building your own technical and personal skills with access to leading tools and training
As a team member whose inputs, suggestions and experience are encouraged, valued and appreciated
To be awesome in this role, you will have: 
Skills in R, Python, C#, Microsoft Azure, SQL Server, SSRS, SSIS
 
And experience in:
Data Visualisation tools, such as PowerBI
Master Data Management and tools like Azure Purview
Migration from on-premise data warehouse to Microsoft Azure
API development
Business intelligence, data warehousing or advanced analytics projects
A similar Analyst position for at least 3-5 years with a focus on data management, data governance and data strategy
All phases of software development including requirements analysis, design, coding, testing, defect management
Conducting process mapping and requirements gathering workshops with non-technical stakeholders
 
If you have knowledge of SQL queries, databases and data modelling as well as developing Microsoft PowerApps and Employment Services industry experience, then we would love to hear from you!
 
As a senior team member, you will be a self-motivated individual who thrives on digging into data, problem solving, clearly communicating a meaningful action plan, and creating solutions using a combination of experience, insights, technology and new thinking. 
 
In all our people, we need someone who will naturally live our values.
 •    We’re in it together
•    Never give up
•    Do what’s right
•    Deliver on our promise
 
So, what’s in it for you?
 
Give Some - every role contributes to local communities and local people in some way. A proportion of our profits are dedicated to local projects.
 
Get Some - the perks of being a not-for-profit include salary packaging means you pay less tax and more money each fortnight in your pocket! We offer flexible work options - just ask us what’s possible. And then, there are meals and entertainment perks on top!
 
Grow Some - We are committed to your development and career development. Tell us about your professional development aspirations and we’ll put in place a career plan. We invest in technical and leadership development and encourage internal promotions.  We have awards for being awesome and hope that one day that could be you!
 
Apply now!

Description:
Insurance for Individuals
Youi prides itself on being different. We've challenged the Australian insurance industry since our inception in 2008 and have worked hard to build a strong brand that’s agile and innovative. Our unwavering commitment to our people and our dynamic work culture is the key to our success. So for a career that lets you be you, and rewards you well for your hard work, Think Youi.
About the Role
Working as part of our Business Intelligence (BI) team, sitting within the ‘Product’ department, you can expect to be dealing with people from right across the organisation from the CEO to Call Centre Advisors. The BI team are responsible for bridging the gap between IT (systems) and the business using data analytics to assess processes, determine requirements and deliver data-driven recommendations and reports to management and stakeholders.
You will...

Conceptualise and manipulate data
Design, enhance and supply necessary BI reports to all business areas
Deliver accurate and timely reports available to relevant users
Provide adequate documentation of reports and processes for maintaining reports
Respond to staff queries within the agreed time frame
Assist with ad hoc project and initiatives

The successful candidate will be based at our Sunshine Coast Head Office in Sippy Downs, working a weekly rotation of in office and work from home. Full time work from home employees may be considered - please apply and we can discuss your requests for flexibility at the phone interview stage.
About You

Tertiary education in numerical or IT disciplines preferred but not essential
Previous experience with SQL
Previous experience using a data visualisation tool such as Tableau preferred
Experience working with large data sets
Professional verbal and written communication skills
Solutions-focused, driven to achieve great results
Customer-focused, always wanting to provide awesome service to those you assist

Culture & Benefits 
We are well known for our awesome culture and working environment and award-winning employee experience programs. Combine that with smart casual dress code, Sunshine Coast location, career progression opportunities and onsite cafes, it’s no wonder why our people love coming to work every day! 
How to Apply 
If you’re ready to fast-track your career by adding real value, please "APPLY NOW". We can’t wait to meet you!

Description: Business Intelligence Analyst The Reporting and Insights Analyst is responsible for providing vital support to the business by using data analysis and reporting to drive insights and decisions that improve Service operations. This role will work cross-functionally with key stakeholders across business leaders to identify business optimisation initiatives, deliver reporting solutions and support the business in implementing key analytical initiatives. The Analyst is responsible for supporting business managers with Optus Business in the identification and execution of opportunities for continuous service improvement, journey optimisation, and relentless focus on customer service optimisation across our Voice and Digital Channels. You’ll be a self-motivated individual who thrives on digging into data, problem solving, clearly communicating a meaningful action plan, creating solutions improving service journey’s using a combination of experience, insights, technology and new thinking.  To be successful you’ll have sound analytical ability to problem solve, some knowledge of experience design, understanding the importance of creating seamless Omni-channel experiences across service journeys. Using modern business intelligence tools, you will undertake critical analysis of data and information to achieve improvements in performance measures such as cost reduction, time reduction or quality improvement across the entire Business Care. Your core focus:  Leveraging enterprise wide information assets and system capabilities to design, map, develop and automate reporting. Team player who can work independently to source data from various feeds, while working with various groups from around the organisation to build a simple view of operational insights. Partner with key stakeholders across the business to identify business problems for analysis and reporting to keep them engaged and to resolve the problem together Develop and implement analysis and reporting to resolve business problems (e.g. customer behaviour prediction, market analytics, interaction forecast, resource and operation optimisation, etc.) Develop business intelligence and analysis to report and measure business performance Coordinate analytics projects in an agile way to ensure business value deliverables are maximised Actively identify process improvements and recommend necessary actions to promote continuous improvement culture Support leadership team with timely and accurate data to analyse and represent the current operational performance. Automate reporting (Tableau and like systems). Where Tableau reporting would not be available other automated options will be scoped to limit manual reporting requirements.  The Analyst will be able to understand the reporting requirements from Stakeholders and design and build a simplified reporting view. Time management and prioritisation will also be a key skill, along with managing stakeholder expectations.  You’ll be accountable for executing small projects and supporting larger projects from identifying and fixing broken journey’s to optimising existing experiences through to building new seamless, frictionless service journey’s and experiences for Optus customers with an omni-channel approach. About you:  5 years full time commercial experience of which a minimum of 3 years is in a full-time  (Direct or indirect) management position in a customer services / contact centre environment  Strong stakeholder management Demonstrated experience in managing an operation of significant size and reporting on performance. Proven remote management experience Proficient in systems such as IBM Cognos, EDW, Tableau, Excel, SQL, Alteryx Identify key parameters, assumptions and considerations that impact a development and its business case Identify optimal solutions that balance Customer and market needs with what is realistic, at reasonable cost, in reasonable time and with available resources Advanced Excel data lookup/matching and/or database manipulation skills Anticipate difficulties and identify contingency plans  The perks [link removed] We offer all kinds of benefits, such as: [link removed] ·        Work collaboratively in an open, agile environment with flexible working hours and location·        Discounts with over 400 companies Australia wide (Technology, Retail, Home, Fashion and more!)·        Mobile and Broadband staff discounts·       ·        Training, Mentoring and further learning opportunities·        About us At Optus, we don’t sit back and let the future happen to us – we’re out there making it.  By expanding into new technology and relentlessly improving every day, we’re working to create a better tomorrow for all Australians.

Description:
G8 Education is an ASX 300 organisation and leading provider of quality early education and care services. Owning over 450 Centres and with over 10,000 team members, we are continually expanding and looking to grow and strengthen our network.
About the role:
To provide value added insights to the business that lead to optimal business decisions. Provide in-depth strategic and analytical information in the areas of operations, customer, network growth and portfolio performance management. Build and maintain reports to track key performance indicators.
Key responsibilities include:
• Use Power BI to understand, interpret, and blend large volumes of data from different sources• Use Power BI to build company-wide reports and model data for analysis• Using data analytics to generate insights in the areas of customer experience, operations, marketing and team• Undertake regular reviews of existing portfolio for demographic, economic and commercial drivers• Produce documentation of results and findings, interpret and present back to the business, including to the executive management • Providing relevant and accurate analytical review of the Group’s data and key performance metrics • Creating efficiencies in reporting methodologies• Work with the rest of the FP&A team in developing G8’s data strategy including data dictionary, data integrity rules, documentation requirements, and master data file management• Business partner with departments within the other areas of the business to provide reporting and analytics to drive increased revenue and lower costs• Present information using Power BI to a range of levels in the organisation including executive management
 
Essential Criteria:
• 4+ years’ experience in a similar role• Undergraduate qualifications in finance, business, or a related discipline• High attention to detail• Problem solving skills• High level understanding of data and experience of blending large volumes of data from different sources• Prior experience in extracting, integrating, manipulating, and displaying data from various systems using automation where possible• Power BI experience highly desirable• A good communicator across all levels of the business• Presentation skills • Ability to plan and prioritise workload • Advanced level of Excel modelling skills• Early education sector experience desired • Natural curiosity to ask questions of the data and look for insights• Basic to intermediate SQL knowledge desired
 
Benefits Include:
• Attractive salary package• Generous discount on childcare fees • Exclusive access to our employee benefits program covering a wide range of discounts and promotions • Dedicated focus on professional growth and development
This is a rare opportunity; if you want a diverse, challenging and personally fulfilling role, apply now!
Please note the advertising closing date is indicative only. G8 Education reserves the right to close the advertisement before this date is reached. Therefore, it is encouraged that you submit your application as soon as possible. G8 Education is a committed advocate for child protection, safety and wellbeing. We have a zero tolerance for any form of child abuse or harm. The safety and wellbeing of children will always be our priority and all team members are expected to embrace this shared commitment.G8 Education is committed to ensuring the health and safety of all who attend the premises that it operates. This includes accepting responsibility to provide, so far as is reasonably practicable, a workplace that is safe and without risk to health for all team members, children and members of the broader community. G8 Education requires all employees to have received both vaccinations by 31st January 2022 (or hold a medical exemption), all new employees joining the organisation will also need to meet this requirement.

Description:
Your new companyAt Hays, we are on a journey to become life-long partners to millions of people and organisations. We are proud to be the Industry Leader and understand the important role our people play to ensure we stay the best.
We are bold, agile, and open to new ideas and approaches, whether embracing cutting-edge technologies, developing our people, or innovating the way we work. We know the right person in the right role can change lives and transform the organisation for the better.What you’ll need to succeed in this role:As Junior Business Intelligence Analyst, you will work alongside our Senior BI Analyst and help support the boarder business by analysing and presenting data to inform the decision-making process. You will be responsible for:
Designing, supporting, and maintaining a suite of reports through SSRS, with a view to growth into other reporting platforms (Power BI).
Stakeholder partnering to gather requirements, design, build and deploy solutions.
Analyse data to identify trends and uncover patterns in data and present in dashboards.
Proactively creating and maintaining BI that will assist decision makers and help identify areas for improvement
Assisting with the design and deployment of solutions for contractual requirements of external clients in conjunction with account directors.
To be successful for this role, you will have strong communication skills, the ability to work autonomously and be a self-started. Experience working with SSRS, and advanced SQL knowledge is essential for this role.What you’ll get in returnWe work in a rapidly evolving industry and to help support you in navigating these changes and to enable you to work more efficiently, we invest in your training, development and technology, as well as offer a flexible work environment with the opportunity to work between the office and home.
We encourage diversity of thought to create new ideas and innovate our ways of working and our leadership group is committed to helping you develop your skills and career through on-going training, coaching and support, which could include a move to one of our other 33 countries that we operate in.​
A career at Hays means working with skilled people from diverse backgrounds, in a great atmosphere and with career advancement opportunities.

Description: Great opportunity to join our team at Demant, a global healthcare organisation.  We are looking for a passionate, skilled Business Intelligence Analyst to join a small team working closely with departments across the business to support the use of data and analytics to improve the quality of life of people living with hearing loss.   This is a fulltime role and can be based either at our Macquarie Park Office, Sydney or our Parkside Office, Adelaide.    About Demant Demant is a world-leading hearing healthcare group that offers solutions and services to help people with hearing loss connect and communicate with the world around them. For more than a century, the Demant Group has played a vital part in developing innovative technologies and know-how to help improve people’s health and hearing. Wellbeing centre – an online platform that offers a countless number of online workouts, meditations, nutritional and financial advice – everything you need to live a healthier and happier life Employee Assistance Program Birthday and Christmas gifts   Don't Delay,  Apply Now!    NOTE: We review applications from multiple platforms and invite candidates for interviews continually, so don't delay, submit your application as soon as possible.

Description:
So, this is William Buck:
We believe in Changing Lives!
Forget the 'number crunching' stereotype, this firm is 100% people focused. Our bold brand promise 'Changing Lives' is more than just a brand promise, it's part of everything we do.
William Buck is fast growing a reputation as a place that provides a professional and friendly working environment with a great culture, benefits and clear and progressive career opportunities.
The Opportunity
William Buck are developing innovative new solutions producing insights from data, and we have a fantastic opportunity for a BI Analyst to join our team.  
This is an exciting new role for us and we are looking for an individual who will work closely with our business software developers and the broader technology team to understand our business needs, develop and maintain reports and data visualisations, and develop prototypes that can be further developed into reports and dashboards.
As well as demonstrated technical knowledge, we are seeking a friendly, collaborative team member with fantastic customer service skills, and a problem-solving attitude. 
 
Key responsibilities will include:
Developing strong relationships with stakeholders to capture requirements and business needs
Translate business needs into data models, business intelligence reports, data visualisation dashboards and the underlying data structures that support evidence-based decision making and insights
Assisting with analysis, strategic advice and support across the organisation, with a focus on the use of business intelligence to drive improvement 
Working with data owners to understand the data capture processes and design validation reports to improve data quality processes
Assist with the design and migration to a cloud-based enterprise data warehouse
Provide technical support to the development team as required 
Desired skills and Experience:
Experience in a similar role or an accountant who has gained skills in data analytics or software development
Relevant tertiary qualifications (accounting, computer science, mathematics, STEM) or equivalent experience SQL data extraction and manipulation skills
Demonstrated experience in data warehousing and automated reporting using Power BI or similar
Working knowledge with APIs – RESTful desirable but not essential
Experience working with integration and workflow automation platforms such as Workato, Dell Boomi, Nintex etc. is a plus
Attention to detail, ability to identify technical issues, contribute to business process improvements, and to clearly document progress and solutions
Demonstrated ability to work within a team and independently to deliver high quality results in a dynamic environment.
 
Your application will remain confidential and the successful applicant will have Australian permanent residency or unrestricted Australian working Visa rights.

Description:
Avant is Australia’s leading medical defence organisation with a proud heritage of protecting Australian medical professionals for over 125 years.
Avant now represents 80,000 health practitioners and medical students across every state and territory, delivering market leading products and services to meet their professional, personal and practice needs. Building on this heritage, our vision is to be the most trusted professional partner in supporting doctors throughout their lives and careers.
Being a mutual organisation, owned by members and run purely for their benefit, our members are at the centre of all we do. As well as providing products and services to our member, we play a broader community role by advocating for improvements in the healthcare system and in quality, safety and professionalism in medicine, through delivering education and research activities.
The position
As a Business Intelligence Specialist at Avant, you’ll be joining the Enterprise Information Management (EIM) team within the Group Technology Services (GTS), responsible for helping our business get the most value out of their data. You will be the Qlik Sense guru and data modelling hero that enables our business to conquer the last mile of analytics.
Avant highly values data analytics and we have recently invested a great effort in designing and implementing a state-of-the-art data platform. In this role, you’ll help us extract valuable insights from our data. Using DBT (Data Build Tool) on Snowflake, you model our datasets into the context of our business areas. With your partnering skills, you are able to extract business requirements and translate them into data models and Qlik Sense apps that help our data tell its story. At the end of the day, our stakeholders can make data-driven decisions thanks to your hard work.
This is a full-time permanent position. The team is currently located in Sydney, but working out of one of our other offices is an option (Melbourne, Canberra, Adelaide, Brisbane, Hobart, Perth).
The key responsibilities include:

Collaborate with business stakeholders to extract requirements and design data solutions
Model datasets and build Qlik Sense apps to create the insights our stakeholders need to thrive
Be a thought leader on, and advocate of, data modelling and Qlik Sense best practices and share your knowledge and expertise with the wider analytical community

The key skills needed to be successful in this role

2+ years hands-on experience in within a data-oriented role:
An entrepreneurial, curious, hands-on and problem-solving mindset
The ability to distil user requirements and translate those into a data model and app design
Excellent communication and collaboration skills; enjoyment of working with colleagues from different business areas.
Experience with Snowflake, DBT and/or Python would be looked upon favourably

Why work at Avant?
At Avant, our people are the centre of everything we do for our members. We offer a range of benefits and opportunities to enable you to make a difference, learn, and grow in your career.

Discount of 25% on Private Health Insurance, free Salary Continuance Insurance and free Travel Insurance
We value our people by offering an inclusive workplace with flexible work, career development and internal mobility opportunities.  Our flexible working arrangements are designed to enable genuine work-life balance.
Your development is our priority and we have a variety of learning and development programs that will support you in your career.
Employee Referral Program which rewards $2,500
We offer support to our people via Employee Assistance Program (EAP), Health and Wellbeing programs, Tertiary Education Sponsorship and Support.
We have a diverse and connected work environment where your contribution and ideas will be valued and respected and make a real difference to the lives of others.

Please note:  Avant Mutual is a vaccinated employer.  Prior to the commencement of your employment by Avant, you are required to be fully vaccinated against the Covid-19 virus or have a medical certificate stating that you cannot receive a Covid-19 vaccination for valid medical reasons.  
For further information, please contact our Careers team at careers@avant.org.au

Description:
Business Intelligence Reporting Analyst – Scentre Group BrandSpace 
 
Our story 
Scentre Group is the owner and operator of 42 Westfield living centres in Australia and New Zealand. Our purpose is to create extraordinary places, connecting and enriching communities.
A career with Scentre Group BrandSpace fosters the chance to be part of a team that is transforming the digital media and physical retail space. Work with great people and add value to a tangible product you can see.
Through our extensive Digital Out-of-Home Media and Casual Mall Leasing networks, the BrandSpace team harnesses the full power of the Westfield environment to create meaningful connections between brands, retailers and shoppers.
The Role
We’re seeking an experienced Reporting Analyst to fuel our sales insight capability and enable the effectiveness of a large ANZ sales team, this role reports into the Business Intelligence Manager within the Sales Operations & Strategy team and is responsible for;

Compiling, analysing and reporting on sales data
The creation, build & continual improvement of dashboarding across multiple data sources.
Proactively improving the quality of an insight-driven reporting suite.
Supporting the advancement and automation of the regular sales reporting, analytics and analysis.
Delivering insight led recommendations for process improvement.
Redefining the analytics environment to track network and sales performance.
Generating models to forecast demand and revenue performance.
Generating actionable insights to inform the annual GTM sales strategy.
Executing on the development and delivery of annual sales targets and goal setting.
Developing tools to capture competitor activity and market trends.

What will set you apart from the rest? 
We’re not looking for one specific background, but what will stand out is your ability to generate powerful insights to focus the sales effort and track to performance goals. The distilling of large data sets into simplified, insight-driven dashboards will be second nature. You’ll be able to demonstrate experience not only technically in your career, but also with business partnering too. In addition to your technical capability, you’ll be confident, energetic and driven. You’ll have a history of building a strong rapport with all your stakeholders and thrive in a fast paced and evolving environment.

Motivated in creating performance dashboards and data visualisation?
Commercially minded Analyst with a strong understanding of the drivers of sales performance?
Proven track record of analysing complex datasets to identify trends and produce high quality actionable insights?
A considered a trusted advisor to your stakeholders with a minimum 3-4 years’ experience in a similar role?
An expert at Excel and Tableau/Power BI? Experienced with relational databases >2yrs SQL, Google BQ, Salesforce?

 
 
What sets us apart from the rest? 

Diverse career paths across our vertically integrated business with an in demand Data analytics core focus
Ability to innovate in a company that not only encourages it but will facilitate it
Competitive benefits including 18 weeks parental leave, volunteer days to work with our charity partners, health and wellbeing discounts and ability to purchase extra annual leave
For the second year running we have been named as a Bronze Employer at the Australian LGBTI Inclusion Awards
We’re recognised as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA) and committed to creating a workplace culture in which women and men are equally valued and rewarded

To us, diversity is about recognising and valuing the contribution of people from different backgrounds, with different perspectives and experiences. We believe that all the ways we're different contribute to our success. Diversity includes (but is not limited to) gender, age, disability, sexual orientation, ethnicity, religion and cultural background. Inclusion is promoting and developing a culture where all of us can be ourselves and thrive. It's important to us that our workplace reflects the communities in which we operate, and Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples are encouraged to apply to all roles at Scentre Group.
If this sounds like you, apply today to make extraordinary happen!

Description:
As the third largest local government area in Australia and the fifth fastest growing region, the Moreton Bay Region boasts beautiful beaches and waterways, amazing manufacturing hubs and picturesque hinterland hamlets. Moreton Bay has a strong and connected community that enjoys all the traditional Jinibara, Kabi Kabi and Turrbal country has to offer within our region.
With a diverse workforce of more than 1900 team members dedicated to servicing the needs and enhancing the lifestyle of more than 479,000 residents, each team member has an intrinsic ability to impact our community. Whether you’re a manager or working on the frontline, your role will make a difference - bring your expertise and join our driven team today.
This role sits within our Cultural Services Department, which includes Galleries, Heritage and Museums, Libraries, and Cultural Activation. Cultural Services aim to provide engaging leisure and learning experiences by connecting people to resources and each other. We strive for excellence when delivering exhibitions, information, collections, programs and spaces for our community and visitors. Our department employs approximately 220 staff over 16 venues throughout the region. 
About our opportunity
We have a brand-new opportunity for a passionate and savvy Business Intelligence Officer to provide high quality business and data analysis and intelligence within our Cultural Services team.
Ultimately, this position will play a pivotal role in transforming and developing our cultural service delivery across our region and within our branches of libraries, galleries and museums and cultural activation.
To achieve this, you will:

design, develop and implement innovative and appealing, user-friendly reports and dashboards to build data-literacy at all levels across the department
partner with business units to ensure that processes are reviewed (and documented) and turn information into insights that drive business performance;
provide advice on data management and reporting to ensure data integrity and reliability of reporting sources; and
further develop the department’s data sources and uses of Business Intelligence tools (programs and software)

This could include anything from reviewing and mapping a new process, conducting external research to assist leaders with strategic planning or implementing software that generates real-time and accessible insights and reports.
About you
You will be committed and driven to work and think smarter, using your business and data analysis skills and experience to promote cultural services opportunities.

Description:
Job Title | Analyst (Intelligence) (Environment Officer Class 9)
Employment Type: 2 Temporary roles up to 12 months  with the possibility of extension
What?s on Offer
As an Analyst Intelligence you?ll be:
?    Located at our 4PSQ Parramatta office
?    Earning between $108,841 ? $121,247 pa plus superannuation (dependent on qualifications, skills & experience)
?    Part of the greater NSW Department of Planning & Environment (NSW DPE) cluster
?    part of a world class organisation making a difference to the environment
?    Be part of an inclusive, dynamic and vibrant team culture
Environment Protection Authority Overview
The NSW Environment Protection Authority (EPA) is focused on being a world class regulator and on being the stewards of the environment.  We use all our regulatory tools to protect and enhance the environment we live in today and in the future.  We are responsive and adaptive and: 
?    take action to be the courageous voice of the environment, finding evidence and science-based solutions to some of our most formidable environmental challenges.
?    take a proactive and protective approach to ensure our land, air and water are future-proofed and enhanced for our children and generations to come.
Our mission is to create healthy environments, economies and communities so we can deliver together for the best living on the planet forever. 
EPA people are energised by our purpose and focus on the environment and are:
?    Purpose led making a meaningful difference to the environment, economy and communities delivering varied work and innovative outcome
?    Passionate and committed teams, who care, trust and collaborate to protect the environment and each other.
?    People focused ? We put people first creating a culture where everyone can be themselves, respecting and developing our diverse skills & aspirations and prioritising our safety and wellbeing.
The Opportunity 
Intelligence and Analysis Unit ? Intelligence Analyst role
The EPA Intelligence and Analysis Unit (IAU) leads the development of strategic, operational and tactical intelligence products that inform compliance campaigns, policy development, investigations and stakeholder interactions. As an Intelligence Analyst you will work closely with intelligence practitioners, clients and government partners to provide timely, accurate and readily available intelligence support. Working in a small and motivated team, you will apply an intelligence skillset to key problem areas and identify targeted and effective options for decision-makers to act on. The Intelligence Analyst will also have input into the strategies, policies and governance practices that guide the EPA?s intelligence capability.
Waste Crime Taskforce ? Intelligence Analyst role
The Waste Crime Taskforce (WCT) sits within the EPA?s Major Compliance and Investigation Branch and investigates serious and/or high profile organised waste crime offences with a view to prosecution and plans and executes proactive compliance campaigns and other operations in collaboration with internal and external stakeholders to prevent and disrupt waste crime. The WCT is a multi-skilled team of investigators, lawyers, an intelligence analyst and an operational officer.
The WCT Analyst (Intelligence) provides high quality tactical and operational intelligence advice, assessments and reports to the Chief Investigator and Principal Investigators in support of investigations, compliance campaigns and other operations.  
For more information about this exciting opportunity, click here to view the role description - Ananlyst Intelligence
About you 
Knowledge and understanding of the intelligence cycle and ability to apply it to the issues faced by the NSW EPA.
Understanding and extensive experience of tactical and operational intelligence and ability to apply intelligence concepts.
Ability to prepare intelligence assessments and reports. 
Knowledge of environmental protection policy and related legislation.
Why work for us?? 
Exciting career pathways and opportunities:? 
We offer vibrant and exciting career paths for people from a wide range of backgrounds and skills. Once you?join the?NSW Government, you?ll be supported to develop your skills and expertise through ongoing training, and opportunities to move easily from role to role, and agency to agency across the entire NSW government.? 
 
We provide a safe, supportive, ethical, diverse and inclusive workplace for our people is one of our priorities. We run a variety of programs and provide a range of supporting resources to ensure the wellbeing of all our people.? 
To apply, please submit an updated CV (max 5 pages) and Cover Letter (max 2 pages) outlining your relevant experience and capabilities. 
For further information about the WCT Intelligence Analyst role, please contact Amanda Kelly on Amanda.Kelly@epa.nsw.gov.au or 02 8275 1678
For further information about the I&AU Intelligence Analyst role, please contact Kate Hey-Cunningham on Kate.HeyCunningham@epa.nsw.gov.au or 02 9995 6012. 
Applications close on:  Sunday 20 February 2022 at 11.59pm
Additional Information
A recruitment pool will be created from this recruitment action for ongoing and temporary roles and will remain current for eighteen months for candidates who are successful through the process. If you have been successfully placed on a talent pool in the last 12 months you do not need to reapply
If you are deemed as a recommended candidate following your interview, we will be inviting you to complete various background checks as part of our recruitment process before a final decision is made on the outcome of your application.
Our background checks may include, but are not limited to Reference Checks, National Police Checks, Working with Children and Medical Checks. The background checks will vary depending on the requirements of the role you have applied for and the work and environments you will be working across
Our commitment to diversity and flexibility:
At the EPA, we believe a diverse and inclusive workforce contributes to the success of our business and are committed to ensuring that our workforce reflects the communities of NSW.
We understand that flexibility means different things to different people and are committed to offering flexible work arrangements where and when possible.
Looking for more information or assistance in applying? Our Diversity team can assist to: 
? provide alternative formats to apply
? make adjustments to the recruitment process
? offer information about workplace adjustments and support networks
We encourage people with disability to apply. If you have disability and require more information on adjustments and assistance to apply, contact the Diversity team on Diversity@DPIE.nsw.gov.au (please include reference number). 
If you are an Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander check out Our Mob on Country https://www.dpie.nsw.gov.au/premiers-priorities/our-mob-on-country to see the work we do and get assistance in applying. 
Thank you for your interest in this position. We look forward to receiving your application

Description:
MLC Life Insurance. We have been protecting Australians for over 130 years. We respect the role we play in providing peace of mind for our customers, and we never lose sight of it.
Our Purpose
MLC Life Insurance is one of Australia’s leading life insurance specialists and a member of the Nippon Life Insurance Group, one of the world’s leading insurers. We are guided by our simple purpose: ‘A Promise for Life’. We provide almost 1.2 million Australians with reassurance that they and their loved ones will be supported when they need it most. It’s a promise that provides peace of mind and helps them sleep at night.
Our purpose is supported by Our Values of Do What’s Right, Deliver Together, Make it Simple, Own it and Aim High. It’s how we work together and behave every day in every interaction with our customers, partners and each other that defines who we are. 
Our Strategy
Our strategy puts our customers at the centre of our ambition to be Australia’s leading and most trusted life insurer. It is through the commitment, energy and talent of everyone at MLC Life Insurance, working together, that we make a positive contribution to the lives of our customers. To support all of us to be at their best every day, we offer a flexible work environment centred on development, wellbeing, recognition and contribution. 
With more than 1500 people nationally, we believe our success is built on the unique contribution of our people. Diversity and Inclusion is core to what we believe in and who we are. We aspire for everyone at MLC Life Insurance to feel valued and respected for who they are.
The Role
Reporting to the Manager of Information Architecture & Data Modelling, the Senior Business Analyst will be responsible for leading business requirements activities to augment our Data Warehouse footprint. 
This role will see you create detailed business analysis documents while outlining problems and finding solutions for business data problems. Additionally, you will identify and prioritise functional and non-functional requirements as well as liaising with business users to obtain feedback and approval. You will create specifications to map sources to target and work closely with data modellers to represent requirements as data models and engage with PowerBI developers to ensure accurate visualisation of data requirements.
You will use your demonstrated Business Analyst skills to navigate a new data environment through coordination, planning and conflict resolution to ensure overall team success.
About You
A seasoned Business Analyst with 3+ years experience with a focus on data warehousing and/or advanced analytics projects and with excellent verbal and written communication skills.  
You have proven experience in the usage of business analyst techniques including; elicitation, documentation, interviewing techniques, conducting workshops, process mapping, gap analysis, traceability and business scenarios.
Lastly, your strong understanding of regulatory and reporting requirements coupled with your ability to forecast, budget and provide financial analysis will see you succeed in this role. 
Why Choose Us?
At MLC Life Insurance, you will have the opportunity to:
work with a WGEA cited Employer of Choice for Gender Equality
enjoy flexible work options and an inclusive environment where everyone is respected and valued for who they are and their unique contribution
embrace a culture of customer centricity and an ambition to be Australia’s leading, most trusted Life Insurer
access CircleIn Parental Support - an online support resource for our working parents
access a range of benefits including competitive salary, lifestyle leave, two days volunteer leave every year, recognition of service milestones; and
wellness and lifestyle offerings including access to Uprise – our Digital Wellbeing Program, as well as discounts on a variety of lifestyle and entertainment products and services.
 
Should an applicant be the preferred candidate, background checks (including Federal Police Checks, Employment checks, ASIC banned and disqualified persons and Bankruptcy checks) will be completed prior to the candidate's employment being confirmed. The outcomes of the background checks do not automatically bar candidates, however they will be assessed against the inherent requirements of the position.

Description:
As the third largest local government area in Australia and the fifth fastest growing region, the Moreton Bay Region boasts beautiful beaches and waterways, amazing manufacturing hubs and picturesque hinterland hamlets. Moreton Bay has a strong and connected community that enjoys all the traditional Jinibara, Kabi Kabi and Turrbal country has to offer within our region.
With a diverse workforce of more than 1900 team members dedicated to servicing the needs and enhancing the lifestyle of more than 479,000 residents, each team member has an intrinsic ability to impact our community. Whether you’re a manager or working on the frontline, your role will make a difference - bring your expertise and join our driven team today.
This role sits within our Cultural Services Department, which includes Galleries, Heritage and Museums, Libraries, and Cultural Activation. Cultural Services aim to provide engaging leisure and learning experiences by connecting people to resources and each other. We strive for excellence when delivering exhibitions, information, collections, programs and spaces for our community and visitors. Our department employs approximately 220 staff over 16 venues throughout the region. 
About our opportunity
We have a brand-new opportunity for a passionate and savvy Business Intelligence Officer to provide high quality business and data analysis and intelligence within our Cultural Services team.
Ultimately, this position will play a pivotal role in transforming and developing our cultural service delivery across our region and within our branches of libraries, galleries and museums and cultural activation.
To achieve this, you will:

design, develop and implement innovative and appealing, user-friendly reports and dashboards to build data-literacy at all levels across the department
partner with business units to ensure that processes are reviewed (and documented) and turn information into insights that drive business performance;
provide advice on data management and reporting to ensure data integrity and reliability of reporting sources; and
further develop the department’s data sources and uses of Business Intelligence tools (programs and software)

This could include anything from reviewing and mapping a new process, conducting external research to assist leaders with strategic planning or implementing software that generates real-time and accessible insights and reports.
About you
You will be committed and driven to work and think smarter, using your business and data analysis skills and experience to promote cultural services opportunities.
As a must, you will be able to demonstrate excellent oral and written communication skills, strong data visualisation skills and the ability to translate technical concepts into simple terms. Equally important to be considered, will be your IT skills and experience in data analytics and building Business Intelligence reporting platforms and dashboards.
You are one to embrace challenges with a positive attitude and be comfortable working towards deadlines and managing a variety of tasks in a busy work environment. Committed to providing a high level of customer service, you can foster and build strong relationships with business partners and stakeholders, whilst keeping and organisational mindset and doing what you do best!
Highly regarded, will be applicants who hold a tertiary qualification in Data Science (or similar field) and a Working with Children Blue Card.
Whether you are an emerging data analyst or an established business intelligence guru - this is a truly unique and rewarding opportunity you do not want to miss! Apply now! 
The Details
Term: Permanent Full Time
Award/Level:  Qld Local Government Industry Award (Stream A) - Level 5 of the Moreton Bay Regional Council EBA4 Certified Agreement
Location:  North Lakes Library

$84,340 pa + super (up to 12%) + leave loading
72.5 hour fortnight
9 day fortnight

Why join the MBRC Team?
Aside from an opportunity to build a rewarding career within a diverse and growing organisation, we offer a range of team member benefits including:

Discounted Health Insurance.
Free flu vaccinations every year
Fitness Passport program offering discounted membership for you and your family to selected facilities.
We are proud to offer opportunities to develop your career within a local government organisation and our team members are encouraged to undertake study for career development in their area of employment under our Study, Training & Research Scheme (STARS).
Generous employer and employee super contribution scheme.
Salary packaging options on novated leases, superannuation payments, smartphones and devices.
Free onsite parking. 
We want you to feel well supported when you need it most - as a team member you will have access our 24/7 confidential counselling service, leader support hotline, chaplaincy program and our mates and construction program.
Flexibility at MBRC depends on the type of work you do but could include options such as work from home, part time, 9-day fortnights and flexible days. Talk to us about what flexibility means to you!

Description:
Senior Tech Business Analyst- Analytics  
WIB - Treasury Technology
Sydney based, Max term role
How will I help?
As a Senior BA, working with Group Treasury, your main role will focus on Treasury Front Office’s Qlik Sense self-service analytics platform that integrates with existing Treasury data assets, thus extending data capabilities, and empowering Treasury to undertake data analytics of the Group's balance sheet at a customer account level.
What you will do
Engage with business owners and relevant stakeholders to elicit business needs
Generate artefacts to document business needs, issues and outcomes including user stories and business requirement documents, stakeholder mapping, data flows, process mapping and data catalogues. 
Actively participate in all phases of the project including analysis, design, development, testing, user training, change management and implementation.
Rapidly acquire working knowledge of customer’s internal line-of-business systems
Define data element requirements including history, timeliness and frequency of data
Design the technical data mappings from source to target including transformation rules
Eliciting business requirements through stakeholder engagement.
Delivering technical specifications for the scrum team.
Identifying issues and opportunities relating to the performance of the application.
Data and systems analysis including: Identifying new sources of data to meet business requirements, defining business rules, solving data integrity issues, Contributing towards data simplification and consolidation initiatives.
What’s in it for me?
You will play an important and significant part in the future of a business that has been around for 200 years. Our vision is to become one of the world’s great service companies. So, we will back you in the development of your career, with internal career prospects and flexible working. You will also be backed by a fantastic team of people in a can-do, supportive structure.
What do I need? 
Minimum 5 years of Data BA or Technical BA experience
Intermediate knowledge of SQL, Excel with VBA and other Microsoft Office applications
Experience with data visualisation tools like Power BI / Tableau
Experience in Qlik Sense and QlikView is highly desirable
Extensive experience of delivering high quality analysis outcomes & successful projects and building relationships & managing a diverse range of stakeholders with different objectives. 
Experience working in Agile / Scrum teams
In depth knowledge of Treasury & Investment Banking products and Risk measurement. 
Experience of working in Institutional Banking project is preferred 
Banking experience (esp. Treasury) is ideal

What is it like to work there?
As well as good pay and a great culture, joining the Westpac family means you will get some of the best banking, wealth and insurance benefits in the market. We back our employees by helping them work towards industry-recognised qualifications, using online learning, training modules and career planning tools for you to grow with us. We will even pay you to do volunteer or community work.  As an equal opportunity employer, we are proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility – and champions inclusion.
How do I Apply?
Start here. Just click on the APPLY button.
As part of our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, this role is open to experienced candidates seeking a discussion around workplace flexibility. We invite candidates of all ages, people with a disability and Indigenous Australians to apply.
The health and wellbeing of our employees is our top priority. We’ve developed clear standards to ensure our people are confident, safe and healthy whether they’re working from a Westpac Group site or working from home. These are based on expert medical advice and Safe Work Australia guidelines.
The Westpac Group has implemented an Entry to Workplace Policy that requires employees and others entering our workplaces to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 by relevant dates set out in the policy (subject to applicable medical exemptions). Our employees are required to comply with the policy regardless of whether they are in customer-facing or non-customer-facing roles (as employees in non-customer-facing roles are required to attend the workplace under our Hybrid Working Strategy). Further, the Westpac Group is required to comply with State/Territory issued public health orders/directions which require relevant workers to be vaccinated against COVID-19 to enter workplaces.
By applying for this role, you acknowledge that you are aware of our Entry to Workplace Policy, and if you secure employment with us, you will be required to comply with the policy.

Description: INNOVATION thrives here  WHY BAI COMMUNICATIONS It's an exciting time to be part of BAI Communications. As a leading communications infrastructure provider, our technical excellence is sought after around the world. Building on our ground-breaking achievements, we continue to expand our operations, helping connect people, support communities and advance economies.  At BAI Communications, we keep Australians, from the cities to the outback, connected, and the significance of what we do is felt by everyone. Our critical communications team actively protect our sites and keep services on air. We work alongside authorities, to operate the NSW Government Radio Network and provide life-line communications to NSW Telco Authority emergency service providers who manage public safety. We are incredibly proud by the commitment, hard work and leadership our people show every day. Our trusted Field Service teams ensure continuity of our network. Our highly skilled Operators keep the public informed during times of crisis and react quickly to changing operational requirements of a demanding complex network. Our deep engineering, delivery and operational capability make us the partner of choice for the government and industry stakeholders alike.  During times of crisis, such as bushfire or cyclone season, our people travel from around the country to support this critical work. We care for our People. Volunteers for local Fire Service or State Emergency Services are provided with additional time off work at full pay for their volunteering activities. Hiring contractors fill gaps in our usual work and we are therefore always interested in hearing from people looking for permanent or casual work. We continue to develop world-class solutions for new and emerging technologies. This includes planning for future network improvements which allow our customers to take advantage of technology innovation. Description: Your role:As an Intelligence Analyst – System Operator (known in the Navy as Cryptologic Systems Operators) your role supports classified Government intelligence programs by analysing signal transmissions; and informing tactical and military advantage both at sea and ashore. This diverse and mentally stimulating role encompasses a range of specialist skills that support intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance activities. You’ll use sophisticated, state-of-the-art search receivers and other complex equipment to intercept, record, analyse and disseminate the intelligence of signal transmissions. Teamwork is an important part of the role. You’ll work in a close-knit team that really rely on each other. There are also many opportunities for career growth and travel; all while making a difference to the defence of Australia and her interests.As an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator, you will receive training in the  following areas:- Analytical techniques and methodical problem-solving,- Communications theory and networks,- Methods for working with intelligence information,- Preparation and presentation of intelligence briefs, and,- Provide advice to Commanders and other audiences as required. Prior experience isn’t needed. You’ll gain all the necessary skills and qualifications to become an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator as part of your training. Although, it is worth noting that successful Operators typically have a sound background in mathematics and are comfortable with the fundamentals of physics.Life in the Navy: A career in the Navy is challenging and highly rewarding, and comes with good work/life balance, competitive salary and skills for life. You can expect to feel a unique sense of accomplishment and pride from serving and protecting our country and helping to keep our vast coastlines safe.Life in the Navy is anything but mundane. You’ll enjoy varied lifestyles, rewarding careers, opportunities to travel, and excellent social and fitness facilities, free medical and dental; all in a dynamic and fulfilling working environment. Don’t worry, it’s not all life at sea—there’s more to the Navy than ships, submarines and helicopters. Some days, you might be exploring exciting new countries with your fellow crewmates. Other days, you could be stationed locally not too far from home. Salary: Upon completion of your initial military and initial employment training, you’ll enjoy a competitive starting salary package from $75,625 including service and uniform allowances. You will also receive a Maritime Allowance when serving on ships. In addition to your salary, you will receive generous superannuation, housing subsidies and free medical and dental care.Apply Now: For this role, you must be over 17 at time of enlistment, an Australian Citizen and have passed Year 10 English, Maths and Science (physics is preferable).Click the APPLY button if you think you have what it takes to become an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator and we’ll get in contact with you shortly.You can also visit the link below to view the full position description and learn more about life in the Navy.https://navy.defencejobs.gov.au/jobs/intelligence-analyst-systems-operatorThe Australian Defence Force is an equal opportunity employer. This advertisement is to ensure women are aware of the rewarding and fulfilling careers available in the Navy, Army and Air Force. Females are encouraged to apply, however all roles are open for Australian men and women to apply.

Description:
Marketing Data Analyst

Permanent role
Flexible location

About the role
The Marketing Science Analyst should help shape strategic marketing agenda by supporting the Marketing Science Lead and Marketing Science Operations Lead in generating and delivering insightful analysis highlighting potential opportunities to deliver growth, maximise ROI and connect marketing performance with business outcomes.
The Marketing Science Analyst will play a key role across the marketing science value chain in processing data for analysis, building models, and creating presentations that communicate impactful insights and putting forward actionable recommendations to marketing stakeholders.
Key Duties

Development of innovative and proactive marketing performance insights using expertise in data mining and analysis tools.
Unify analytics with business acumen to partner with internal stakeholders to work through challenging marketing planning decisions and unique business questions
Responsible for developing models and tools, identifying and creating models to help understand, monitor, and predict marketing outcomes. Eg. Make and optimize budget, channel and media mix decisions, understand the impact of a marketing activity on sales, forecast the impact of budgeting, brand and competitor activity on business outcomes.
Harmonise, process, and analyse data to develop presentations which address marketing & business challenges
Ensure statistical models and all deliverables are of high quality and meet the internal quality control guidelines
Work with team to continuously evolve our statistical methodologies and develop new ways of solving complex business problems. Collaborate with internal & external partners to help develop new tools and capabilities
Develop and maintain strong working relationships with key management groups particularly Technology, Customer & Market Insights, Finance and Portfolio teams.  
Support the maintenance and improvement of processes used to collect, retrieve, and interpret data.
Handle large and complex marketing data using different applications.
You will be expected to work closely with marketing teams to help them understand the impact of decisions on potential results and to generate unique insights that ‘solve the puzzle’ of what drives performance.
Establish strong working relationships with key internal stakeholders and agencies identifying shared goals, removing blockages, and enabling collaboration.
Manage stakeholder expectations and act as an advocate for marketing science practices.

About You

Bachelor’s degree or above (ideal areas of study/related study include: Business Analytics and Management, Economics, Actuarial Studies, Statistics, Mathematics, and/or Marketing)
1-2 years of experience with marketing mix modelling, digital media analysis, business focused analytics, advertising effectiveness analysis, quantitative market research or other related client insights experience.
Proficient working knowledge of Microsoft PowerPoint and Excel; other tools such as SQL & R a plus but not required.
Highly analytical with strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
Experience working independently to identify themes across data points and the ability to communicate a story with the data.
Comfortable working with a team developing and presenting presentations using insights derived from analytics.
An understanding of how to use data to solve complex business questions and drive business solutions.
The ability to occasionally travel domestically and/or internationally.
Strong verbal and written communication skills suitable for audiences all at levels of the business (Brand Managers, EGMs, CEOs, Board).

Technical Competencies

Graduate in marketing or computer science
Strong numeracy and analytical skills
Demonstrated experience using data mining tools
Passion for data interpretation and optimisation
Experience with relational databases and analysing large quantities of marketing data
Exposure to Dashboard development desired
Team player, creative and passionate
Ability to multi-task while demonstrating a high level of attention to detail and organization
Outstanding presentation and communication skills
Comfort dealing with large amounts of data on a regular basis
Evidence of using and applying data to aid decision making and analysis
Ability to learn quickly and adapt to fast-changing environment
Demonstrated ability to work independently in processing data and communicating insights.
Experience with tag management platforms, Excel, APIs, etc. will be highly regarded.

Description:
Avant is Australia’s leading medical defence organisation with a proud heritage of protecting Australian medical professionals for over 125 years.
Avant now represents 80,000 health practitioners and medical students across every state and territory, delivering market leading products and services to meet their professional, personal and practice needs. Building on this heritage, our vision is to be the most trusted professional partner in supporting doctors throughout their lives and careers.
Being a mutual organisation, owned by members and run purely for their benefit, our members are at the centre of all we do. As well as providing products and services to our member, we play a broader community role by advocating for improvements in the healthcare system and in quality, safety and professionalism in medicine, through delivering education and research activities.
The position
As a Business Intelligence Specialist at Avant, you’ll be joining the Enterprise Information Management (EIM) team within the Group Technology Services (GTS), responsible for helping our business get the most value out of their data. You will be the Qlik Sense guru and data modelling hero that enables our business to conquer the last mile of analytics.
Avant highly values data analytics and we have recently invested a great effort in designing and implementing a state-of-the-art data platform. In this role, you’ll help us extract valuable insights from our data. Using DBT (Data Build Tool) on Snowflake, you model our datasets into the context of our business areas. With your partnering skills, you are able to extract business requirements and translate them into data models and Qlik Sense apps that help our data tell its story. At the end of the day, our stakeholders can make data-driven decisions thanks to your hard work.
This is a full-time permanent position. The team is currently located in Sydney, but working out of one of our other offices is an option (Melbourne, Canberra, Adelaide, Brisbane, Hobart, Perth).
The key responsibilities include:

Collaborate with business stakeholders to extract requirements and design data solutions
Model datasets and build Qlik Sense apps to create the insights our stakeholders need to thrive
Be a thought leader on, and advocate of, data modelling and Qlik Sense best practices and share your knowledge and expertise with the wider analytical community

The key skills needed to be successful in this role

2+ years hands-on experience in within a data-oriented role:
An entrepreneurial, curious, hands-on and problem-solving mindset
The ability to distil user requirements and translate those into a data model and app design
Excellent communication and collaboration skills; enjoyment of working with colleagues from different business areas.
Experience with Snowflake, DBT and/or Python would be looked upon favourably

Why work at Avant?
At Avant, our people are the centre of everything we do for our members. We offer a range of benefits and opportunities to enable you to make a difference, learn, and grow in your career.

Discount of 25% on Private Health Insurance, free Salary Continuance Insurance and free Travel Insurance
We value our people by offering an inclusive workplace with flexible work, career development and internal mobility opportunities.  Our flexible working arrangements are designed to enable genuine work-life balance.
Your development is our priority and we have a variety of learning and development programs that will support you in your career.
Employee Referral Program which rewards $2,500
We offer support to our people via Employee Assistance Program (EAP), Health and Wellbeing programs, Tertiary Education Sponsorship and Support.
We have a diverse and connected work environment where your contribution and ideas will be valued and respected and make a real difference to the lives of others.

Please note:  Avant Mutual is a vaccinated employer.  Prior to the commencement of your employment by Avant, you are required to be fully vaccinated against the Covid-19 virus or have a medical certificate stating that you cannot receive a Covid-19 vaccination for valid medical reasons.

Description: About the RoleThe purpose of the Business Systems and Data Analyst role is to enhance business systems usage to extract more value and provide ease of use; and to facilitate effective data governance and reporting to support accurate business decisions.The role responsibilities include: Improve business value of IT systems by working with business managers and IT support teams to enhance core business systems and their data repositories, including Salesforce, Atlassian Confluence and Jira, and Microsoft SharePoint. Work collaboratively with business managers and executives to determine data analytics and dashboard requirements. Support quantitative data analysis by administering data analytical platforms (PowerBI, Salesforce reporting etc.) and providing data catalogues, user training, report templates and default system connectors/integrations. Define and administer a metadata schema within SharePoint Online to increase searchability and support data classifications. Ensure data and business systems adhere to security policies and procedures. Ensure core business systems (including SharePoint, Teams, Atlassian, S/4Hana and Salesforce) have defined, documented and communicated governance standards aligned to best practice and nationally recognised security frameworks. Assist with minimising administrative effort across the business using process automation. Develop and maintain a “Champion” program providing key staff with training and expertise to accelerate the uptake and value of core systems. Analyse system data sources (AD, Azure, SaaS, etc.) to ensure consistency and improve IT Governance and functional excellence. Assist other South Asia Esri distributors with aligning on business and data systems and policies.  About You A minimum of three years’ experience in business systems administration and data governance within similar environments. Experience with programming languages such as Python, PowerShell, T-SQL and Apex. Experience with industry-standard security governance frameworks (e.g., NIST CSF, ISO 27001, ISM, COBIT or Essential Eight). Keen interest in business technology, including self-education and keeping up to date with industry changes. Strong interpersonal / client engagement skills. Excellent written and verbal communication skills. Highly motivated and proactive. Strong attention to detail and accuracy when accomplishing a task. The ability to prioritise workloads, manage time and schedule tasks whilst remaining resilient to changing priorities. Advocating for, and experience in presenting data-driven information. Understanding of ITIL aligned business processes, including best practice organisational data flows. The ability to foster teamwork and promote a positive and inclusive workplace experience, in-office and online. Demonstrated alignment with Esri Australia's core values. Tertiary qualification in an associated business discipline (Information Technology, Data Analytics etc.) is highly desirable. Accreditations and Certifications in related disciplines is highly regarded (Microsoft Certified Data Analyst Associate or Cloud vendor security certifications: Microsoft Azure Data Scientist Associate or AWS Certified Big Data) You must hold current permanent and full-time working rights in Australia. Personality/behaviour aligns to Esri Australia’s core values.  For further details or if you have any questions, please contact Tibo Torche, National Talent Acquisition Lead on 07 3218 0448 or mail to ttorche@esriaustralia.com.au. We are a 2022 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant.Please note that Esri Australia does not accept unsolicited resumes from recruiters or employment agencies.
