Description: Why work with us?Firstly, the perks are pretty amazing! We offer amazing flexibility, ongoing learning and development so you can have an amazing career, AND an incredible environment to work in, both online and in the office!But that's not all… There's a heck of a lot more perks that are going to blow your mind! Just ask!Who is RMIT Online?We bring the best digital methodologies and people to online education, focussed on meeting the needs of the future of work. Our whole online courses range from short, 'snackable' credentials to full undergraduate and postgraduate programs. With a heavy focus on digital skills and emerging technologies, our portfolio of courses is co-designed and co-delivered with world-leading industry partners.We empower our people to do the best work of their life; you're valued for your expertise. Like our students, we are a team of lifelong learners with a growth mindset culture. Being open, collaborative and outcome-driven really pays off; and we have fun while we're at it!Let’s talk about youWith strong analytical and creative problem-solving abilities, you have proven ability to evaluate large data sets to extract meaningful and actionable insights and quickly understand business processes, systems and data sets. As a data guru, you find comfort in complex Excel spreadsheets and know your way around visualisation software such as Tableau and Power BI; experience with Salesforce is a big bonus!You thrive in fast moving environments and can multi-task like a pro. You enjoy the opportunity to work across multiple teams to frame and solve problems through analysis. Bonus points for a sense of humour, grace under pressure, knowledge of the higher education sector and/or experience in management consulting!Sounds great! Tell me about the role This is a critical role that reports to the Chief Student Experience (SX) Officer analysing student experience data to generate insights we can action to improve our student experience. This could lead to a career path into the strategy or knowledge teams, depending on whether you want to take a consulting track or a specialist track into data and knowledge. In this role you’ll be responsible for analysing, reporting and developing insights across a range of datasets – including students, teachers, and delivery partners - to diagnose issues or opportunities to improve our student and partner experience. You’ll also work alongside the Knowledge Team to identify and source appropriate datasets to generate insights across a range of business functions, and collaborate with the Knowledge Team and our Business Intelligence Guild to represent SX reporting/analytics requests, design and deliver self-service tools and dashboards for internal stakeholders, identify ongoing improvements and implement effective data governance and user training across the SX team. What’s a week in the life of this role?Always a new challenge and with loads of variety, you could be doing a range of short analytical pieces, scoping strategic pieces of analysis and debriefing insights from recently completed analysis. You’ll be continuously collaborating with various parts of the business and deep-diving into data to identify actionable insights. How to apply?Send us your CV now along with a brief cover letter telling us about:Why you’re the best person for this job and why you want to work for RMIT OnlineWhat was the most interesting data set you have evaluated and extracted meaningful information that you turned into actionable insights and how did it impact the business.Need more convincing?We have an amazing, social office in the heart of Melbourne that includes a rooftop terrace, open workspace, and more. We currently work in a hybrid model, which means a blend of working from home and working from our office.We pride ourselves on being a respectful, diverse and inclusive community of fun and intelligent people. RMIT is an equal opportunity employer committed to being a child-safe organisation. We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community.

Description: Join one of Victoria's leading not for profits and be a part of something big  Competitive Salary + Tax reducing salary package Full-Time, Ongoing Role     A little bit about us For over 165 years we have been in Victoria assisting people through the challenges of poverty and exclusion address suffering, advocating against inequality and promoting human dignity and self-determination. Overall, St Vincent de Paul Society Victoria has many arms and services. These include soup vans, education programs, home visitation programs and VincentCare Victoria, which provides a range of services and programs for people who are experiencing or at risk of homelessness and disadvantage. This includes crisis accommodation, drug and alcohol dependency programs, and housing. It’s an exciting time to join the organisation as we have recently launched a new strategic plan that is future oriented and full of exciting initiatives. The IT Transformation team will play a pivotal role in delivering on strategic projects and helping the organisation to achieve operational excellence.    A little about the Role The Business Intelligence Lead will play an integral role in the organisation and in the delivery of our strategy. Reporting to the Manager IT Transformation, this role will add value through the development of BI reports, dashboards, and applications to create greater visibility and inform business decisions Week to week you will work with your manager to prioritize projects; oversee the technical execution of BI projects encompassing research, design and implementation of data platforms, data pipelines, data models, reports/dashboards and data-driven applications. You will design and implement processes to mitigate data quality issues. As a good collaborator you will work closely with team members and the other teams within organization to plan, coordinate, and deliver according to a high-level roadmap. We have a lot of work to do in this space. In your first year you will work on:  Design, implement and maintain the overall Power BI, ETL and data warehouse environments and operation; Complete the funding contract data management project Work with the leadership team to develop reports and dashboards to provide greater visibility and insights for the organisation Work closely with the IT Transformation team to understand the data behind our key processes and identify and establish improvement in data capture to increase data integrity and improve the consistency in coding structures Work with the team to develop a digital mindset across the workforce to foster a culture of evidence-based decision making and innovation And plenty of other interesting initiatives…    A little bit about you You are currently working in a similar role and have experience in Power BI visualisation and moving, manipulating and analysing data between different programs. You are known for being responsive, approachable, and service oriented, you will confidently build connections with your key stakeholders and create positive working relationships. You will be enthusiastic, highly organized, detail orientated and driven by a commitment to delivering exceptional results. You will bring a "hands on" approach and be a proactive operator who thrives on developing relationships to achieve high stakeholder engagement. We love a bit of humour in the team too! Work should be enjoyed, not endured. More specifically you will have:  A formal qualification in Information Technology or a minimum of 3 years of Business Intelligence experience (required). Advanced Power BI visualisation and report navigation design (required). Strong SQL skills, including views, stored procedures and functions (required). Experience in Power BI visualisation and DAX measure development. Strong project management skills to deliver multiple projects on time and work autonomously in a high-pressure, deadline driven environment A high level of experience in moving data between programs, manipulating data and analysing large data sets. Hands on experience in querying and extracting data across multiple, disparate and complex relational databases. The ability to communicate, both verbally and written, clearly and concisely at all levels.     Why work for us?  We offer:  Salary packaging, sometimes called salary sacrificing is a huge attraction here! It is a popular way of providing employees in the community sector with tax benefits over and above their salary. It means the real value of a salary package can be significantly higher than the nominal value. We are committed to professional development to make sure that your career keeps growing while you’re working with us. We like to have a laugh and you will always find some sort of chocolate or cake in our work area… be prepared! We make an incredible difference in the lives of over 300,000 people every year. We believe in families, so we like to provide a family-friendly environment in which to work. We offer a place where you know you are contributing to an organisation committed to helping others. We are passionate about #Social Justice. We have some great talent who are happy to share their experience and skills to help you on your way. We are complex in our design which always makes work interesting.    Where good happens # Goodworks   If making a difference in your local community is important to you and you meet our essential requirements we can’t wait to hear from you. Please send us your updated CV and a cover letter that tells us a little more about you and why you would be perfect for the role. Please click here for a copy of the Position Description.     Applications close: Please don’t delay in submitting your application as applications will be reviewed upon submission.   Please note that prior to any commencement of employment, pre-employment checks must be completed these will include reference checking, a national criminal history and right to work check, proof of COVID-19 vaccination, and a working with children check.   St Vincent de Paul Society Victoria is proactive in supporting child safety We value diversity and aim to build an inclusive environment that champions, embraces and respects differences.    We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, and people of all abilities, cultures, sexual orientations, and gender identities and expressions.

Description: Coordinator, Service Delivery - BI, Analytics and Reporting  Ongoing role  Location: Bathurst or Sydney  We are proud of our diverse regional team and welcome flexible working. Regular travel may be required to engage with the team and our partners at our home base in Bathurst.  About Us  Spatial Services is a division of the Department of Customer Service. We are a key provider of spatial land information services in New South Wales. Our integrated framework provides comprehensive land and property services including property, surveying and mapping information to the people, businesses and government agencies of NSW, as well as nationally and internationally.  Some of our key initiatives include: Sourcing information from organisations and individuals to compile maps, databases and informationMaking information public availability for land management purposes, state economic and social development, and for planning and providing government services to the community, including event and emergency managementOverseeing the practice and conduct of surveying in NSW through the Surveyor General.About the Role  This role reports to the Service Delivery Manager and is responsible for managing the continuous improvement of our Spatial Services product and services portfolio. This role has three focus areas: business intelligence, analytics and reporting. As our Service Delivery Coordinator, you will be the lead in these areas of endeavour and be responsible for undertaking data analysis and provide specialist advice on the key focus areas to support the strategic development and business development of Spatial Services. In addition, you will utilise business intelligence tools and applications to provide insight on business performance and product development opportunities.  On a day to day-to-day basis you will: Generate reports and liaise with key internal stakeholders to inform business decisions.Lead exploratory analyses to uncover customer insights to improve the digital customer experience.Be part of a small leadership group and make recommendations for improvement, identify changes and recommend actions.Mentor and train a small team to ensure performance standards and personal development objectives are met.Proactively profile, analyse and interpret campaign data and results, and then use the discoveries to improve future solutions, analyses and recommendations.About You  The successful candidate will have a responsibility of managing priorities in a high-volume environment as well as providing specialist advice and making prompt decisions while ensuring client expectations and business objectives are met.  To be successful in this role you will have: Relevant experience and qualifications/training in a similar field.Genuine interest in/and ideally proven experience in business intelligence, analytics and reporting.Understanding of the products and services that may be associated with Spatial Services.Experience in using Spatial Services related business, administrative, information and financial systems.Experience using a range of software applications including but not limited to Splunk, Microsoft Suite including Excel, Power BI, Python and JIRA.A motivated team player who can work in independently as well as in a team environment.An inquisitive mind - will you investigate something unusual in the data if it wasn't what you were looking for?Strong interpersonal skills to engage with people at all levels of the organisation and build strong relationship and trust with clients and internal stakeholders.Learn More  For enquiries relating to the role, please email Shaun Bunyan at shaun.bunyan@customerservice.nsw.gov.au.  How to Apply  Your application must include a covering letter and an up-to-date resume that details your knowledge, skills and experience in relation to the above role, demonstrating your capability against the focus capabilities of the role.  Please submit your CV (5 page maximum) with a maximum two-page cover letter outlining how your experience meets the focus capabilities of the role.  Salary Grade 7/8, with the base salary for this role starting at $99,431 base plus superannuation  Click Here to access the Role Description. For enquiries relating to recruitment please contact Lucinda Pham via Lucinda.Pham@customerservice.nsw.gov.au.  Based on our current Work, Health and Safety (WHS) requirements, and in line with our Mandatory Vaccination Policy, it is a condition of engagement for a role within Service NSW/Department of Customer Service that staff be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. Description: Your role:As an Intelligence Analyst – System Operator (known in the Navy as Cryptologic Systems Operators) your role supports classified Government intelligence programs by analysing signal transmissions; and informing tactical and military advantage both at sea and ashore. This diverse and mentally stimulating role encompasses a range of specialist skills that support intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance activities. You’ll use sophisticated, state-of-the-art search receivers and other complex equipment to intercept, record, analyse and disseminate the intelligence of signal transmissions. Teamwork is an important part of the role. You’ll work in a close-knit team that really rely on each other. There are also many opportunities for career growth and travel; all while making a difference to the defence of Australia and her interests.As an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator, you will receive training in the  following areas:- Analytical techniques and methodical problem-solving,- Communications theory and networks,- Methods for working with intelligence information,- Preparation and presentation of intelligence briefs, and,- Provide advice to Commanders and other audiences as required. Prior experience isn’t needed. You’ll gain all the necessary skills and qualifications to become an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator as part of your training. Although, it is worth noting that successful Operators typically have a sound background in mathematics and are comfortable with the fundamentals of physics.Life in the Navy: A career in the Navy is challenging and highly rewarding, and comes with good work/life balance, competitive salary and skills for life. You can expect to feel a unique sense of accomplishment and pride from serving and protecting our country and helping to keep our vast coastlines safe.Life in the Navy is anything but mundane. You’ll enjoy varied lifestyles, rewarding careers, opportunities to travel, and excellent social and fitness facilities, free medical and dental; all in a dynamic and fulfilling working environment. Don’t worry, it’s not all life at sea—there’s more to the Navy than ships, submarines and helicopters. Some days, you might be exploring exciting new countries with your fellow crewmates. Other days, you could be stationed locally not too far from home. Salary: Upon completion of your initial military and initial employment training, you’ll enjoy a competitive starting salary package from $75,625 including service and uniform allowances. You will also receive a Maritime Allowance when serving on ships. In addition to your salary, you will receive generous superannuation, housing subsidies and free medical and dental care.Apply Now: For this role, you must be over 17 at time of enlistment, an Australian Citizen and have passed Year 10 English, Maths and Science (physics is preferable).Click the APPLY button if you think you have what it takes to become an Intelligence Analyst – Systems Operator and we’ll get in contact with you shortly.You can also visit the link below to view the full position description and learn more about life in the Navy.https://navy.defencejobs.gov.au/jobs/intelligence-analyst-systems-operatorThe Australian Defence Force is an equal opportunity employer. This advertisement is to ensure women are aware of the rewarding and fulfilling careers available in the Navy, Army and Air Force. Females are encouraged to apply, however all roles are open for Australian men and women to apply.

Description:
Marketing Data Analyst

Permanent role
Flexible location

About the role
The Marketing Science Analyst should help shape strategic marketing agenda by supporting the Marketing Science Lead and Marketing Science Operations Lead in generating and delivering insightful analysis highlighting potential opportunities to deliver growth, maximise ROI and connect marketing performance with business outcomes.
The Marketing Science Analyst will play a key role across the marketing science value chain in processing data for analysis, building models, and creating presentations that communicate impactful insights and putting forward actionable recommendations to marketing stakeholders.
Key Duties

Development of innovative and proactive marketing performance insights using expertise in data mining and analysis tools.
Unify analytics with business acumen to partner with internal stakeholders to work through challenging marketing planning decisions and unique business questions
Responsible for developing models and tools, identifying and creating models to help understand, monitor, and predict marketing outcomes. Eg. Make and optimize budget, channel and media mix decisions, understand the impact of a marketing activity on sales, forecast the impact of budgeting, brand and competitor activity on business outcomes.
Harmonise, process, and analyse data to develop presentations which address marketing & business challenges
Ensure statistical models and all deliverables are of high quality and meet the internal quality control guidelines
Work with team to continuously evolve our statistical methodologies and develop new ways of solving complex business problems. Collaborate with internal & external partners to help develop new tools and capabilities
Develop and maintain strong working relationships with key management groups particularly Technology, Customer & Market Insights, Finance and Portfolio teams.  
Support the maintenance and improvement of processes used to collect, retrieve, and interpret data.
Handle large and complex marketing data using different applications.
You will be expected to work closely with marketing teams to help them understand the impact of decisions on potential results and to generate unique insights that ‘solve the puzzle’ of what drives performance.
Establish strong working relationships with key internal stakeholders and agencies identifying shared goals, removing blockages, and enabling collaboration.
Manage stakeholder expectations and act as an advocate for marketing science practices.

About You

Bachelor’s degree or above (ideal areas of study/related study include: Business Analytics and Management, Economics, Actuarial Studies, Statistics, Mathematics, and/or Marketing)
1-2 years of experience with marketing mix modelling, digital media analysis, business focused analytics, advertising effectiveness analysis, quantitative market research or other related client insights experience.
Proficient working knowledge of Microsoft PowerPoint and Excel; other tools such as SQL & R a plus but not required.
Highly analytical with strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
Experience working independently to identify themes across data points and the ability to communicate a story with the data.
Comfortable working with a team developing and presenting presentations using insights derived from analytics.
An understanding of how to use data to solve complex business questions and drive business solutions.
The ability to occasionally travel domestically and/or internationally.
Strong verbal and written communication skills suitable for audiences all at levels of the business (Brand Managers, EGMs, CEOs, Board).

Technical Competencies

Graduate in marketing or computer science
Strong numeracy and analytical skills
Demonstrated experience using data mining tools
Passion for data interpretation and optimisation
Experience with relational databases and analysing large quantities of marketing data
Exposure to Dashboard development desired
Team player, creative and passionate
Ability to multi-task while demonstrating a high level of attention to detail and organization
Outstanding presentation and communication skills
Comfort dealing with large amounts of data on a regular basis
Evidence of using and applying data to aid decision making and analysis
Ability to learn quickly and adapt to fast-changing environment
Demonstrated ability to work independently in processing data and communicating insights.
Experience with tag management platforms, Excel, APIs, etc. will be highly regarded.

Description:
About us
Treasury Wine Estates (TWE) is one of the world’s leading wine companies.  We know that it’s the thinkers, makers and doers who have the most impact as we continue to strive towards being recognised as the world’s most admired premium wine company.  We are proud of our portfolio of brands that have tremendous heritage, rich quality and a reputation for excellence across the globe.  From the iconic luxury of Penfolds, to the broad appeal of Lindeman’s and newer brands like 19 Crimes, we are committed to creating memorable wine experiences for our consumers.
About the role:
Reporting to the Supply Sustainability Manager, the purpose of this role is to support the business and functions by ensuring relevant processes and systems are implemented to ensure compliance to regulations and effective management and integrity of Sustainability Data globally. 
Focusing on our sustainability data, systems and reporting. It will play a critical part in transforming TWE systems and data and analytics capability. This role will directly support the empowerment of our business leaders with data and insights to support better decisions, improve processes and ensure we improve our environmental and overall sustainability footprint.

Continually refine and improve our approach to data collection to ensure consistent, complete, and accurate global sustainability data 
Build a culture and process to support an enhanced focus on data
Lead the manipulation, collation and reporting of data to build stakeholder confidence and engagement
Ensure our approach, process methodology is compliant with relevant technical standards and meets reporting requirements
Conduct verification to ensure accurate data and insights to meet internal and external reporting requirements 
Managing external assurance and drive programs that respond to opportunities for improvement
Lead the development, implementation and transition to a more mature reporting system 
Deliver core environmental and sustainability systems improvements to support strategic initiatives
Actively support TWE continuous improvement and change management processes 
Develop next level analytics including analysing and generating reports of trends, gaps and opportunities to improve performance
Building and developing robust, sustainable and effective analytical solutions

About you
With a Bachelor's Degree in environmental sciences or science related field you will have proven experience in sustainability focused role in either consulting or a corporate organisation.
Expert user of environmental reporting systems including implementation and development of a supportive culture and processes
Strong experience working in data and analytical disciplines including systems such as Power BI and Power APPS. Able to clearly explain insights and develop action plans to respond to improvement opportunities
Expert knowledge of relevant environmental regulations, policies and technical standards. and ability to apply them effectively to data 
Demonstrated success in delivering effective and high-performance analytical solutions.
Good communication skills and the ability to engage with various stakeholders.
Excellent interpersonal skills, including influencing skills.
Experience in improvement methodologies and approaches such as Lean is advantageous
What’s in it for you
Financial Review Boss Best Places to Work winner 2021
Access to the world’s most admired wines through our employee product allowance
True flexibility in determining how, when and where you work to achieve your potential
Global opportunities across Australia & New Zealand, the US, Asia, UK/Europe
Opportunity to build a career across multiple functions (we’re really good at doing this!)
Structured development programs to support your health, wellbeing and career
“TWEforME Day” – an additional day of leave each year, for you to do you
Meeting-free Monday mornings (we all love this!)

Culture
We bring our whole selves, we’re courageous and we deliver together – that’s our DNA.  We’re a passionate bunch who enjoy working together, like to have fun and keep things down-to-earth.  We’re brave enough and care enough to have the right conversations to get the best outcome and are famous for our can-do attitude.  We’re definitely “glass half full” people and see challenges as opportunities and move with pace to achieve our goals.
If you’re ready to help us be the world’s most admired premium wine company, please apply now!

Inclusion and Diversity
Just like the wide range and variety of brands in our wine portfolio, TWE embraces diversity and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin or on the basis of disability.  If you require any assistance to be included in our process, please contact recruitment@tweglobal.com [link removed], quoting the job title and reference number.



How to apply
We move quickly at TWE and continually review applications, so if you don’t want to miss out, apply today.  Note that we prefer to deal with you directly; we haven’t briefed a recruitment agency on this role and won’t be accepting CVs through any recruitment agency, so please apply directly.
In light of COVID-19, we are frequently reviewing our recruitment processes.  Right now, we are conducting all interviews virtually.  This is a fluid situation and we will adapt our processes as we need to with any government guidelines or regulations.

Description:
Marketing Data Analyst

Permanent role
Flexible location

About the role
The Marketing Science Analyst should help shape strategic marketing agenda by supporting the Marketing Science Lead and Marketing Science Operations Lead in generating and delivering insightful analysis highlighting potential opportunities to deliver growth, maximise ROI and connect marketing performance with business outcomes.
The Marketing Science Analyst will play a key role across the marketing science value chain in processing data for analysis, building models, and creating presentations that communicate impactful insights and putting forward actionable recommendations to marketing stakeholders.
Key Duties

Development of innovative and proactive marketing performance insights using expertise in data mining and analysis tools.
Unify analytics with business acumen to partner with internal stakeholders to work through challenging marketing planning decisions and unique business questions
Responsible for developing models and tools, identifying and creating models to help understand, monitor, and predict marketing outcomes. Eg. Make and optimize budget, channel and media mix decisions, understand the impact of a marketing activity on sales, forecast the impact of budgeting, brand and competitor activity on business outcomes.
Harmonise, process, and analyse data to develop presentations which address marketing & business challenges
Ensure statistical models and all deliverables are of high quality and meet the internal quality control guidelines
Work with team to continuously evolve our statistical methodologies and develop new ways of solving complex business problems. Collaborate with internal & external partners to help develop new tools and capabilities
Develop and maintain strong working relationships with key management groups particularly Technology, Customer & Market Insights, Finance and Portfolio teams.  
Support the maintenance and improvement of processes used to collect, retrieve, and interpret data.
Handle large and complex marketing data using different applications.
You will be expected to work closely with marketing teams to help them understand the impact of decisions on potential results and to generate unique insights that ‘solve the puzzle’ of what drives performance.
Establish strong working relationships with key internal stakeholders and agencies identifying shared goals, removing blockages, and enabling collaboration.
Manage stakeholder expectations and act as an advocate for marketing science practices.

About You

Bachelor’s degree or above (ideal areas of study/related study include: Business Analytics and Management, Economics, Actuarial Studies, Statistics, Mathematics, and/or Marketing)
1-2 years of experience with marketing mix modelling, digital media analysis, business focused analytics, advertising effectiveness analysis, quantitative market research or other related client insights experience.
Proficient working knowledge of Microsoft PowerPoint and Excel; other tools such as SQL & R a plus but not required.
Highly analytical with strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
Experience working independently to identify themes across data points and the ability to communicate a story with the data.
Comfortable working with a team developing and presenting presentations using insights derived from analytics.
An understanding of how to use data to solve complex business questions and drive business solutions.
The ability to occasionally travel domestically and/or internationally.
Strong verbal and written communication skills suitable for audiences all at levels of the business (Brand Managers, EGMs, CEOs, Board).

Technical Competencies

Graduate in marketing or computer science
Strong numeracy and analytical skills
Demonstrated experience using data mining tools
Passion for data interpretation and optimisation
Experience with relational databases and analysing large quantities of marketing data
Exposure to Dashboard development desired
Team player, creative and passionate
Ability to multi-task while demonstrating a high level of attention to detail and organization
Outstanding presentation and communication skills
Comfort dealing with large amounts of data on a regular basis
Evidence of using and applying data to aid decision making and analysis
Ability to learn quickly and adapt to fast-changing environment
Demonstrated ability to work independently in processing data and communicating insights.
Experience with tag management platforms, Excel, APIs, etc. will be highly regarded.

Suncorp is a leading financial services provider in Australia and New Zealand, enabling more than nine million customers to better protect and enhance their financial wellbeing. With a heritage dating back to 1902, we have grown to become a top-50 ASX-listed company with over 13,000 people. We offer banking, wealth management and insurance products and services through our well-recognised brands including Suncorp, AAMI, GIO, Apia, Shannons and Vero, as well as those from our partners.
Working within the Suncorp Network we believe we are our best when our workforce is as diverse, talented and passionate as the communities in which we live and operate, and where our people feel included, valued and connected.  We are passionate about inspiring our people by creating an inclusive culture, offering flexible work, career development and internal mobility, and building connected relationships amongst our team members and with our customers. Joining Suncorp, you will be joining an organisation which cares and is proud of our achievements in being recognised for:

Best Insurance Company in Corporate Social Responsibility (2018)
Employer of Choice for Gender Equality for sixth consecutive year (2014-2019)
Money magazine’s Bank of the Year and Business Bank for fourth consecutive year (2018-2021)
General Insurance Product Innovation of the Year (2018)

Description: We are Australia's largest superannuation fund, here to help members achieve their best possible retirement outcome. Working with a wide range of stakeholders, we create meaningful value for members and our communities through our diverse workforce of highly competent and highly motivated employees. Flexible and inclusive work environmentExciting growth plans, both locally and internationallyDeliver outcomes for our MembersYour new team  Our Technology Services group has a strategic remit to uplift, govern and run the Fund's technology capability. It is a highly respected team, with a leadership group who advocate for their people, are open and approachable, committed to providing excellent results, and who share their knowledge. This is your opportunity to join us as we grow and modernise technology services to support Australia's leading Superannuation Fund and more than 2.4 million Members.  Your new role  Reporting to the Governance and Reporting Manager, the Data and Reporting Analyst is responsible for the development and maintenance of the Technology Services dashboard reports, supporting the Leadership team's requirements across risk, performance and governance.  Your responsibilities will include; Incorporate data analysis into designated ongoing reportsUse analysed data to create reports, identifying process improvement opportunitiesUnderstand business requirements to provide clear guidance on delivering actionable insights through visualisation and dashboardsPulling data to develop recurring or one-time reports as requestedBuilding dashboards for Technology Services to present a visualisation of Material Risk analysisMaintaining databases, spreadsheets and other tools used in data analysis, specifically PowerBI and Microsoft ExcelLocating and fixing errors in reports, make recommendations to resolve issues with the underlying data structures to enable improved reporting capabilitiesTraining Technology Services colleagues on how to use and create reportsSupport evidence-based decision making - including appropriate and simple metrics that provide solid data for informed decision making, such as business strategy alignment, cost/benefit, and cost/quality/riskDrive technological innovation as a key enabler of short- and long-term business performance though active participation in the PowerBI COE and champion PowerBI growth and development across the FundWhat you'll need  The successful applicant will have experience with building PowerBI dashboards and demonstrate the ability to wrangle data to ensure that dashboards are updated regularly. In addition, you will bring; 2-3 years' experience in a data analyst or reporting roleStrong technical knowledge of PowerBIExperience with SQL scripting and coding modelsAbility to document business requirementsCritical thinker with strong analytical and problem-solving skillsAbility to identify issues and areas for improvement through analysisInnovative, creative and curious with a strong growth mindsetCollaborative, articulate and persuasiveHigh level of personal integrity as well as the ability to professionally handle confidential mattersMost importantly, you are innovative, creative and curious with a strong growth mindset and have a willingness to believe in and work towards the enterprise purpose and vision.  What you'll get in return  You will be working with a manager who values and supports your personal growth, in a growing, dynamic and authentic organisation that promotes integrity and puts members first. Other benefits include a competitive salary, genuine flexible working arrangements, discounted travel, income protection insurance and generous leave entitlements.  We are committed to the recruitment, development and support of a diverse workforce into an environment which is inclusive, embraces diversity in all its forms and is a place where you can be you. All roles can flex at AustralianSuper and we're happy to discuss what this can look like for you.  We are proud to be a WGEA certified Employer of Choice for Gender Equality (since 2012) and to be recognised as one of Australia's top 10 workplaces for Dads.   What's next  Please apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.  Be Inspired, Be Bold, Be You  Agencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by AustralianSuper's Recruitment team. We will contact our preferred agency partners should we require additional support. Thank you.

Description: Senior Data Analyst Salesforce - NSW GovernmentLocation: Parramatta, Sydney, with great WFH flexibilityRate: $900 - $980 per day + SuperContract Length: 12 monthsNote: Must have extensive prior experience as a Data Analyst or Senior Data Analyst working with Salesforce.We are currently seeking experienced Salesforce Data Analysts for our NSW Government client who will be responsible for design and enhancement of Salesforce dashboards for the Department and wider Executive teams.Keys to Role: - You have extensive prior experience as a Data Analyst or Senior Data Analyst working with Salesforce. - You have a track record of working consultatively with colleagues to meet stakeholder expectations while providing a professional, consistent and reliable approach to customer service. - You manage competing priorities in a high demand environment, and manage stakeholder expectations about analysis outcomes, including with staff and stakeholders who may not have a background in data analysis.- You have prior experience implementing, or working to a well-defined Reporting Process and Data Governance Framework.The OpportunityRight now, we have an opportunity for a Senior Data Analyst (Salesforce) to join us for a 12-month contract in a new customer-focused directorate. Following a review of a critical, customer-facing business process, a large program of work has commenced to redesign process, policy and procedure, and enhance the accessibility, visibility and governance of customer data to drive improvement initiatives.The primary purpose of the role is to design (or enhance) Salesforce dashboards for the Department and wider Executive teams, lead the implementation of a Reporting Process and Data Governance Framework, and support the directorate by creating reports and analysing data from the Salesforce CRM as required. You will: * Lead the design and implementation of dashboards for executives at the Department and the School level via a consultative process. * Lead the development of additional levels of themes in the Salesforce CRM to enhance the usefulness of the current data, and work with the operational teams to ensure they are implemented effectively. * Support the development of detailed business cases and customer satisfaction surveys by extracting and analysing data from the Salesforce CRM as required. * Lead the development and implementation of a Reporting Process and 'front door' system for reports. * Lead the implementation of a Data Governance Framework.

Make a difference to the national mission of our world-leading University, its students and staff  
Enjoy workplace flexibility and be part of a supportive team. 

About ITS
Information Technology Services (ITS) delivers digital solutions that enable the Australian National University to achieve its strategic goals: a student experience equal to the world’s best, and research that transforms society and creates national capability.  ITS has responsibility for the University’s digital ecosystem and is leading the delivery of the Digital Master Plan, a 10-year strategic roadmap for the transformation of the University’s digital capability.  
About this role 
Are you looking to take the next step in your career, have a solid foundation in Data Integration Analysis? ITS is seeking a suitably qualified, highly motivated individual with a successful record of achievements as a data integration analyst.
The Data Integration Analyst is responsible for supporting the provision of business and data analysis services by building effective and collaborative relationships with ITS, functional groups, College and Service Division representatives, and all other internal and external business stakeholders. Reporting to the Technical Lead, Integration Services the successful candidate in this role will support the delivery of integration services on time, budget and to customer quality expectations. The role requires supporting the application of appropriate technical and management skills along with best-in-class methodologies and approaches.
For further information please contact Dr April Weiss, Associate Director, Application Services E: april.weiss@anu.edu.au

A cover letter or ‘pitch’ describing how your skills, experience and approach align with the role - maximum 2 pages.   
A current curriculum vitae (CV) which includes the names and contact details of at least two referees (preferably including a current or previous supervisor). If your CV does not include referees you can complete these online when prompted in the application form.

Description: About the OrganisationOur client is a large Federal Government Department looking to engage a high performing APS6 Data Analyst for a 6 month contract, with possible extension.The roleThe Issue Strings project (the project) is based within the Business Intelligence and Quality Improvement (BIQI) Team within the Complaints Management and Education Branch (CMEB).The CMEB provides a high-quality parliamentary complaint resolution and Public Interest Disclosure service to the public. The BIQI Team is responsible for managing the Office’s business intelligence function through reporting. We support business areas across the Office to access and utilise data and analytics through Power BI.The goal of the project is to improve our current data taxonomy through the development and implementation of a consistent set of issue strings across the Office. Additionally, the project aims to introduce governance mechanisms for the development of future issue strings.Ideal candidate:We are seeking an individual with experience in reporting, who has strong skills in excel, live case management databases, and Power BI or similar analytical reporting tools. The individual will work autonomously with some guidance, as part of a small geographically dispersed team. The individual will use their research skills and stakeholder engagement skills to identify, propose and implement an improved data taxonomy. The individual will also use their strong excel and analytical skills to map existing issue strings to new issue strings. The individual will use their knowledge of live case management databases to implement the new issue strings into our case management system, Resolve.Key duties:Review how issues have been used in internal and external reporting and identify issues to be remedied.In consultation with stakeholders where required, develop a small number of high-level, systemic issues to be used for data across the Office.Define sub-issues based on the current agency- and organisation-specific issues.Modify the current issue string hierarchy to fit the new high-level issues and changed hierarchy.Update Resolve (the case management system) with the new issue strings.Run a Pilot of the testing of the new issue strings and remedy any issues where required.Map the new issue string hierarchy against the current issue string hierarchy for the purposes of Power BI reporting.Introduce a governance framework for introducing new issues and develop user guidance for the use of the new issue strings where required.Hhow to ApplyShould you be interested on this role please send your cv via SEEK or call Francesca Avelluto on 0261627332 for a confidential discussion (or email favelluto@dfp.com.au)DFP welcomes applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds and people with disability. In addition, DFP will provide reasonable adjustments for individuals with disability throughout the recruitment process. If you identify as a person with disability and require adjustments to the application, recruitment, selection and/or assessment process, please advise via adjustments@dfp.com.au or 1300 337 000 and indicate your preferred method of communication (email, phone, text) so we can keep in touch and meet your accessibility needs.Note: You may be required to provide evidence of your COVID-19 vaccination status.

Description:
About Us
Imagine using your experience to help people around the world to hear again. We can offer a unique opportunity to join Cochlear, an iconic Australian company, leading the world in implantable hearing solutions. Our mission is to help more people to hear.
The Opportunity 
This is a fantastic opportunity for an Analyst - Operational Insights to develop predictive analysis techniques to deliver forecast modelling and historical trending through the analysis of our supply chain data. This role will be responsible for providing actionable information through reports and dashboards that utilise existing IT infrastructure.
Key Responsibilities 
The Analyst - Operational Insights role will play a significant role in the determination of the production plan and provide headcount forecasts based on the latest information

In this role you will be responsible for:                     
Maintaining key operational metrics that relate directly with operational performance and have clear links to financial outcomes
Using predictive analytical techniques to help drive better decisions in the determination and prioritisation of improvement projects that will result in efficiency, productivity and yield gains
Delivering real time information to production teams and managers so that they can be more effective in their decision making and focus by developing dashboards using our latest software systems

Why is this role right for you?

Degree qualified in engineering, computer science, statistics or related disciplines
Strong analytical and detail-oriented aptitude
Ability to time effectively, set priorities and meet deadlines
Understanding of Good Manufacturing Practice (GMP)
Ideally, have process improvement experience with business intelligence and visualisation tools such as Tableau, OBIEE in a medical device or highly regulated industry

This is your chance to be part of a premier organization with a great culture, working in a dynamic, growing and rapidly evolving environment to deliver outstanding results that benefit our customers every day. Be part of something purposeful and APPLY now by clicking on the link below and see your career grow!
Cochlear Summary
Cochlear’s mission is to help more people to hear. Around the world, more people chose a Cochlear-branded hearing implant system than any other. Our employees tell us that the number one reason they enjoy working for Cochlear is the opportunity to make a difference to people’s lives. Learn and grow with us as we tackle the most complex challenges in helping people to Hear Now. And Always. Cochlear is the global market leader in implantable hearing solutions including cochlear implant systems (CI) and bone anchored hearing aids (Baha™).

Description:
Application Closes: 08 February 2022
Role: Public Health Intelligence Inbox Coordinator, Reporting & Insights (Fixed term - Full time until 30 June 2022)
Number of vacancies available: 1
Office Location(s): 50 Lonsdale Street/Work from home
Position Summary: 
The Public Health Intelligence (PHI) Inbox team operates as the central point of contact for requests relating to COVID-19 data, reports and epidemiological advice.
This role undertakes a customer-focused approach in the coordination of COVID-19 requests including ensuring stakeholder expectations are being both managed and responded to in a timely manner. 
Work collaboratively with key stakeholders to continuously improve service delivery and enhance operational standards.
Responsibilities 

Coordination and distribution of key information and advice to identified stakeholders on a range of COVID-19 public health issues. 
Operate as an effective team member by delivering quality, timely and effective customer service to a range of stakeholders.

Promote and develop relationships and linkages with key areas across the Data, Intelligence, Modelling and Epidemiology branch within the COVID-19 Public Health Division.

Undertake administrative tasks to support the successful operation of the PHI inbox team's objectives including ensuring all enquiries and requests are appropriately prioritised, managed and reported in a timely manner.
Contribute to the full life cycle of projects to meet departmental objectives including:

a)     Assisting in research, analysis and implementation of projects based on defined outcomes and outputs.
b)     Supporting the development and delivery of projects or sub-projects and their successful delivery and completion within resourcing, timeline and budget parameters. 
c)     Contributing to the monitoring and evaluation of projects to ensure departmental objectives are met.

Where responsible for overseeing, monitoring or delivering projects, ensure they are delivered in accordance with relevant legislation and government regulations, guidelines and standard operating procedures. 
Keep accurate and complete records of your work activities in accordance with legislative requirements and the department's records, information security and privacy policies and requirements.
Demonstrate how the actions and outcomes of this role and work unit impact clients and the department's ability to deliver, or facilitate the delivery of, effective support and services.
Other duties as required.

Mandatory Vaccination policy:
The department is committed to providing and maintaining a working environment which is safe and without risk to the health of its workers and clients. As it is an essential element of any role within the department that employees be able to attend work onsite and to do so safely, employees are required to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 as a condition of their employment. This requirement applies unless they have a medical condition which means they cannot be vaccinated against COVID -19. Therefore, the department will ask any prospective employee, who has been identified as the preferred candidate for a role within the department, to provide proof of their COVID-19 vaccination status prior to any offer of employment being made.  If a prospective employee has a relevant medical condition which means they cannot be vaccinated against COVID-19, they should contact the department to discuss their individual circumstances.
 
HOW TO APPLY:
Applicants are encouraged to apply online, submitting a cover letter and a current resume.
Please note: For this position, you are not required to address each of the key selection criteria in a separate written document.
Preferred candidates will be required to complete pre-employment screening, including a national police check and misconduct screening.
Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa. Work eligibility will be checked as part of the recruitment process.
For further information please visit the Department of Health <https://www.vic.gov.au/department-health>
Click 'Apply Now' to submit your interest in this position.

Description:
Opportunity to work on a high impact transformation
Looking for experienced R programming specialists
Duration until 30 January 2023

Opportunity to work on a key program at the Reserve Bank of Australia, delivering a new analytics platform that will be at the core of our economic insights and reporting. 
We are looking for an experienced Senior Data Analyst to work on a highly visible project involving a complex SQL multidimensional data warehouse, reporting and analytics solution for APRA-sourced data which is used to analyse and forecast liquidity and other nationally critical data in the Australian financial system.
You’ will be working with senior economists and IT program professionals to deliver a bespoke and high profile analytics and reporting system which is critical to the Bank’s work.
In this role you will:

Collaborate with business and IT stakeholders to develop, maintain and optimise data collection and related statistical reporting to provide timely, accurate, and accessible data for economists' informed decision-making.
Independently assess and document current business standard and ad-hoc complex reporting and data analysis requirements including calculations.
Analyse and document user stories and business requirements for a new data analytics platform using agile based and traditional methods
based and traditional methods
Transform data from multiple sources using R programming to produce automated data analytics, visualisations and statistical reports.
Ensure ongoing data integrity, reporting data inconsistencies and resolving these in close collaboration with stakeholders.

Your team
This role is within the Financial System Group which monitors, researches and reports on the payments system and stability of the financial system.
You will work closely with mature and high performing cross-functional Scrum teams within the RBA and with APRA. The work environment is collaborative, friendly and supportive.
Your background
To be successful in this critical role you will possess:

Advanced experience designing and developing efficient code, functions and scripts that leverage data from multiple sources using R and SQL programming languages.
Ability to facilitate workshops or meetings with business and technical stakeholders and external parties at various levels.
Demonstrated experience in data extraction, manipulation and data management.
Advanced knowledge of database and business intelligence concepts and tools.
Any IT technology expertise involving solution design / database development desirable.
Strong written communication skills and concise and succinct communication style.

Your development & career
Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the Australian people, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports people’s growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility.
About the RBA
The RBA pursues national economic policy objectives and undertakes a range of associated activities in financial markets and banking. It also issues Australia's banknotes and operates infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contributes to the welfare of the Australian people.
Our people have a critical role to play in achieving these objectives, whether directly or in a supporting capacity. As a values driven organisation, our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry, we treat one another with respect, while promoting the public interest in our efforts. 
The Reserve Bank of Australia is an equal opportunity employer.  We are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace and encourage applications from experienced candidates seeking workplace flexibility.

Gather, prepare data and undertake detailed analytics of General Insurance portfolios – measuring performance loss ratios, business mix, exposure, rate movement

Description:
Who are we?
Capricorn is a member-based financial services organisation which exists to improve the lives of over 24,000 Members across Australia and New Zealand by supporting them in building stronger automotive businesses. We provide products and services including trade credit, risk protection, equipment finance, trade events, travel services, fuel cards and more. Last financial year Member purchases exceeded $2.59 billion and Member returns exceeded $71 million.
The role and what we are looking for:
The Data Privacy Business Analyst is responsible for current state analysis and risk assessment and will work with business and technology stakeholders to deliver improved data privacy management processes and technical solutions.
Key responsibilities of the role will include:
         Work closely with technology and business SMEs to undertake analysis of current data and records assets and information systems and processes         Conduct SME workshops to elicit current state information         Work with key stakeholders to conduct privacy risk assessment and rating and solution prioritisation         Contribute to definition of privacy business benefits and metrics         With the Data Privacy Project Manager, work with technology platform and business owners to define and deliver sustainable data privacy management processes and technical solutions         Define the scope of data privacy management projects in collaboration with the Project Manager and key stakeholders         Develop functional requirements, specifications, and process documentation for data privacy solutions         Work with technology platforms and Solution Architects to formulate solution designs         Define acceptance criteria and validate testing outputs to ensure solution requirements are met
We're also looking for candidates with the following experience:
         Demonstrated knowledge of business analysis techniques and project methodologies         Experience in business analysis practices including process modelling         Ability to clearly articulate complex topics to a wide audience         Strong understanding of IT systems and operational data privacy requirements         Strong understanding of Australian and New Zealand privacy legislation         Advanced skills in Microsoft Office including Excel, Project, PowerPoint, Visio and Word         Excellent written and oral communication skills with the ability to engage stakeholders at all levels

Proven experience with data privacy or data      management/governance initiatives 

A great place to work
When you join Capricorn, you join a community of people who enjoy coming to work and a company that genuinely invests in their employees. Our culture is one of our most valued assets, so when we recruit, we look for people that not only share our values but are also excited to celebrate our successes. It is our dedication to creating a great place to work, that has resulted in Capricorn being finalists in the AIMWA Pinnacle Awards for Human Resource Management Excellence for the last two consecutive years. 
Making Capricorn a great place to work is our commitment to providing a diverse and inclusive workplace in which everyone is treated fairly and with respect. We recognise diversity and inclusion as one of our most important resources and this is why we are committed to ensuring our work lives fit in with our personal lives. We offer our employees a flexible working environment, paid parental leave in addition to supporting employee’s individual circumstances. Other great benefits of working with Capricorn include ‘dress for your day’ dress code, wellness program, ability to purchase leave, access to a range of discounts, a fantastic reward and recognition program and plenty of social events to keep our team connected. 
The next steps
If you think you are the right person for this role and you believe in a Member first culture, then please apply now. Applications will be reviewed as they arrive, so it is better to apply sooner rather than later. If you need any assistance or adjustments to fully participate in the application process, please contact HR on (08) 6250 9500.
For further information and detail on Capricorn, please visit our website at www.capricorn.coop/careers.

Description:
Analytics Consultant
Permanent Role/QLD/NSW Location 
About the role: 
We are looking for a passionate Analytics Consultant to join the team in a position where you can really make a difference. As an Analytics Consultant, you will deliver high quality Business Intelligence solutions, and engage closely with users to activate insights that drive business change. You’ll understand the user and solve real user problems using data and analytics whilst providing subject matter expertise on BI initiatives.
Key responsibilities include but are not limited to;

Engage with business stakeholders, understand their pain points, identify opportunities and contribute to developing BI/analytical solutions that can create value for them, solving their most difficult problems
Translate business requirements into an innovative and agile BI solution design that enables an expedited delivery of value to stakeholders
Work within an agile framework to deliver incremental value to business customers throughout BI projects or enhancements to existing BI assets
Analytics Consultants are expected to take the lead and drive outcomes for stakeholder’s while working towards removing external blocker as necessary
Create productive and positive relationships with business and technical stakeholders to truly understand what is important to the users
Commit to required delivery velocity when building, deploying and maintaining BI solutions
Participate in the design and technical development of high-quality BI solutions
Drive a culture of innovation and analytical thinking across the teams.
Optimise & automate processes; utilise monitoring tools to measure efficacy of BI solutions

 
Skills & Experience

5+ years of experience, preferably in Insurance/Banking/Information Technology
Bachelor’s Degree in a quantitative discipline (Science, Tech, Engineering, IT, or Mathematics)
Experience designing and delivering BI solutions in a complex enterprise environment
Strong experience and working knowledge of Tableau, Cognos and ThoughtSpot
Strong experience and working knowledge of sourcing data from core systems, database tools and SQL querying (i.e. Redshift, DB2, Netezza, etc.)
Demonstrated experience in analytical thinking and problem solving
Strong facilitation, influencing and negotiating skills
Strong analytic drive, with a focus on detail as well as the big picture
Ability to quickly learn and adapt to new concepts and an ever-changing environment

 
About Us
Suncorp is a leading financial services provider in Australia and New Zealand, enabling more than nine million customers to better protect and enhance their financial wellbeing. With a heritage dating back to 1902, we have grown to become a top-20 ASX-listed company with over 13,000 people. We offer banking, wealth management and insurance products and services through our well-recognised brands including Suncorp, AAMI, GIO, Apia, Shannons and Vero, as well as those from our partners.
Culture
Working within the Suncorp Network we believe we are our best when our workforce is as diverse, talented and passionate as the communities in which we live and operate, and where our people feel included, valued and connected.  We are passionate about inspiring our people by creating an inclusive culture, offering flexible work, career development and internal mobility, and building connected relationships amongst our team members and with our customers. Description:
Application Closes: 08 February 2022
Role: Public Health Intelligence Inbox Coordinator, Reporting & Insights (Fixed term - Full time until 30 June 2022)
Number of vacancies available: 1
Office Location(s): 50 Lonsdale Street/Work from home
Position Summary: 
The Public Health Intelligence (PHI) Inbox team operates as the central point of contact for requests relating to COVID-19 data, reports and epidemiological advice.
This role undertakes a customer-focused approach in the coordination of COVID-19 requests including ensuring stakeholder expectations are being both managed and responded to in a timely manner. 
Work collaboratively with key stakeholders to continuously improve service delivery and enhance operational standards.
Responsibilities 

Coordination and distribution of key information and advice to identified stakeholders on a range of COVID-19 public health issues. 
Operate as an effective team member by delivering quality, timely and effective customer service to a range of stakeholders.

Promote and develop relationships and linkages with key areas across the Data, Intelligence, Modelling and Epidemiology branch within the COVID-19 Public Health Division.

Undertake administrative tasks to support the successful operation of the PHI inbox team's objectives including ensuring all enquiries and requests are appropriately prioritised, managed and reported in a timely manner.
Contribute to the full life cycle of projects to meet departmental objectives including:

a)     Assisting in research, analysis and implementation of projects based on defined outcomes and outputs.
b)     Supporting the development and delivery of projects or sub-projects and their successful delivery and completion within resourcing, timeline and budget parameters. 
c)     Contributing to the monitoring and evaluation of projects to ensure departmental objectives are met.

Where responsible for overseeing, monitoring or delivering projects, ensure they are delivered in accordance with relevant legislation and government regulations, guidelines and standard operating procedures. 
Keep accurate and complete records of your work activities in accordance with legislative requirements and the department's records, information security and privacy policies and requirements.
Demonstrate how the actions and outcomes of this role and work unit impact clients and the department's ability to deliver, or facilitate the delivery of, effective support and services.
Other duties as required.

Mandatory Vaccination policy:
The department is committed to providing and maintaining a working environment which is safe and without risk to the health of its workers and clients. As it is an essential element of any role within the department that employees be able to attend work onsite and to do so safely, employees are required to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 as a condition of their employment. This requirement applies unless they have a medical condition which means they cannot be vaccinated against COVID -19. Therefore, the department will ask any prospective employee, who has been identified as the preferred candidate for a role within the department, to provide proof of their COVID-19 vaccination status prior to any offer of employment being made.  If a prospective employee has a relevant medical condition which means they cannot be vaccinated against COVID-19, they should contact the department to discuss their individual circumstances.
 
HOW TO APPLY:
Applicants are encouraged to apply online, submitting a cover letter and a current resume.
Please note: For this position, you are not required to address each of the key selection criteria in a separate written document.
Preferred candidates will be required to complete pre-employment screening, including a national police check and misconduct screening.
Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa. Work eligibility will be checked as part of the recruitment process.
For further information please visit the Department of Health <https://www.vic.gov.au/department-health>
Click 'Apply Now' to submit your interest in this position.

This intern makes sure their customers are safer and more productive through insight-driven decisions that sustainably captures more value from mining operations. One particular Enterprise Software Suite is a data analytics hub that nurtures collaboration. It helps mines access, see downstream effects, and make decisions from operational technology data. It provides data visualisation, accessibility, data analytics and reporting by connecting and structuring data from Planning, Operations, Safety and Drill & Blast systems.    The Role: The Enterprise Software portfolio team is currently seeking an experienced Application Engineer/BI/Data Software Consultant to join their Perth-based team on a permanent full-time basis. This role has been created due to growth, and your direct report is here in Perth to guide you through this new position. You are the voice of the customer and internal support teams and you will provide clear feedback to the software development team to better the solution for all customers. This position is responsible for driving customer adoption the suite of solutions that deliver on a vision to connect data across the life-of-mine value chain.    Skills and Experience Required: > Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering / Software Engineering, or related fields> Proven experience within a similar position (software solution consulting). Good time management and the ability to work with disparate teams is essential. > Prior experience with technology in the mining industry (planning, operations, drill & blast, safety). Global experience desirable.> Experience with Microsoft Power BI, Tableau and Microsoft SQL Server or Postgres.> Experience in the testing and validation of technology products and development of training courses to assist internal lead experts.     As an individual who can consolidate findings of software usage in the field across different customers it is essential that you have the technical aptitude to interpret and respond to customer requirements, in addition to the soft skills to explain the benefits to management and sales teams. Customer Success: > Provide technical sales assistance to regional teams including trials and demos.> Provide guidance on best practice use of our client's products.> Primarily provide 2nd tier support to escalated requests from the regional service & support teams.> Attend customer sites and regional offices for technical knowledge transfer.> Assist with building key reference sites for our BI system in each region.> Provide global guidance for all major commercial deals including RFI and RFP’s. Having past consulting and training experience will be of value. What’s on Offer:Apart from a salary package that is commensurate with your skills and experience, you will also benefit from the following:> Personalised training and upskilling opportunities for career development for both technical and soft skills.> Work with a diverse, talented, multi-disciplinary team across the globe, gaining valuable skills and knowledge servicing some of the biggest names in the industry.> International and domestic travel to a variety of locations for client services.> Modern, well-appointed office space with a casual and friendly atmosphere.> Work life balance support.> Social events, team building activities, morning teas, quiz nights and more.Travel: This position involves travel intrastate, interstate, and overseas to support and deploy the products in the field. Language:> Fluent English (written and verbal) is a pre-requisite.> Spanish or Portuguese or other second languages would be very favourable.  What's next?...If you feel like the above is a reflection of you, your skills, and where you want to be in 2022, then nows is the time to take the next step! Want to know more?The consulting team at Beacham Group welcome your telephone enquiry. Description: APRA is seeking a Principal Analyst to join our Authorised Deposit-taking Institutions (ADI) Strategic Insights team within the Data Analytics and Insights branch.  ADI Strategic Insights supports APRA's core functions and has responsibility for producing high quality analysis and reports relevant to the prudential supervision of the banking industry. The team utilise a range of data sources to develop insights and identify risks, including financial, economic and loan-level data. The team also contributes to the design of requirements for banks to report data to APRA.  As part of the team you will provide forward-looking analytics and insights, driving risk-based supervisory judgements and strategic decisions. The Principal Analyst plays a key role in shaping the delivery of data-driven insights and advice to APRA's senior executive, banking supervisors, risk specialists and other Government bodies.  You will work closely with senior specialists across APRA to identify emerging risks and formulate and prioritise key initiatives in response. You will also collaborate with a wide range of both APRA and industry stakeholders, and have an opportunity to lead significant projects that will impact the banking industry.  The successful candidate will have significant experience in the financial services industry, combined with a strong background in data analytics. You will have excellent problem-solving ability along with strong written and verbal communication skills. Experience with database queries and business intelligence tools is desirable. The team use SAS EG, R and Power BI, thus experience with these technologies is desirable but not essential.

The Customer Information Management (CIM) team is responsible for leading the way forward in the development our customer centric capabilities. Joining Westpac has many benefits besides building a long and stable career. We aim to provide one big, supportive team to help us reach our vision to become one of the world’s great service companies. We invite candidates of all ages, people with a disability and Indigenous Australians to apply. The health and wellbeing of our employees is our top priority. We’ve developed clear standards to ensure our people are confident, safe and healthy whether they’re working from a Westpac Group site or working from home. These are based on expert medical advice and Safe Work Australia guidelines.
The Westpac Group has implemented an Entry to Workplace Policy that requires employees and others entering our workplaces to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 by relevant dates set out in the policy (subject to applicable medical exemptions). Our employees are required to comply with the policy regardless of whether they are in customer-facing or non-customer-facing roles (as employees in non-customer-facing roles are required to attend the workplace under our Hybrid Working Strategy). Further, the Westpac Group is required to comply with State/Territory issued public health orders/directions which require relevant workers to be vaccinated against COVID-19 to enter workplaces.
By applying for this role, you acknowledge that you are aware of our Entry to Workplace Policy, and if you secure employment with us, you will be required to comply with the policy.

Description: We’re the P&N Group, one of Australia’s largest customer-owned banking organisations.  Driven by a genuine belief in the value of mutuality, we strive to achieve success on behalf of our customers, our communities and each other with passion, energy and commitment. We support our retail and business banking customers through a network of 36 branch locations, regional Contact Centres, mobile lending teams and online channels.  Group HQ is in the Perth CBD with regional offices in Coffs Harbour and Brisbane. Our Group values innovation, agility and the ability to develop strong relationships.
