Description:
An exciting new opportunity has become available to join the eCommerce team within the National Buying department of ALDI Stores, based in Minchinbury. This is a permanent full time role.
 
As an eCommerce Analyst, you will be responsible for supporting the eCommerce team by conducting performance analysis in order to optimise sell through, determine opportunities to improve efficiency and monitor revenue. In this role you will focus on delivering actionable insights utilising data from various sources resulting in increased profit and improved customer experience.
 
What we are looking for:
The successful candidate will be able to work in a fast paced, highly dynamic environment and possess strong numerical and analytical skills. With a passion for eCommerce, you will be an outcome driven individual with a keen eye for detail and the ability to meet competing deadlines. Candidates with eCommerce and online retail experience will be highly regarded.
 
Selection criteria:

4+ years’ experience within relevant fields
Demonstrated experience developing and maintaining performance, financial and business reports
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collate and convert data into meaningful insights
Advanced proficiency with the Microsoft Office suite, particularly Excel
Exceptional organisational skills with the ability to adapt in an evolving environment
Understanding of test and learn methods, highly regarded
Strong communication skills; both verbal and written
Ability to perform consistently under high pressure situations
Able to work autonomously and proactively identify areas of opportunity
High level of professionalism and dedication with a positive can-do approach

 
What's in it for you?

Market leading remuneration - $124,900 - $142,500 (including super)
Flexible work options - work from home up to 10 days per month
Great work life balance with 5 weeks annual leave
Be part of a leading international retailer
Work in a team of collaborative, friendly and supportive colleagues

 
Role responsibilities:

Develop and maintain performance, sales and revenue reporting for the team
Undertake monthly / yearly financial reconciliation in line with ALDI compliance requirements
Develop and implement reporting landscape across the team
Extract and collate data from various data sources to provide insights
Develop and present optimisation proposals based on quantitative and qualitative methods
Analyse and assess the performance of products, categories, warehousing efficiency, site traffic and conversion rates in order to determine strategic recommendations and outcomes
Monitor and report on products and transactions based on purchase activity
Provide a range of reports to the eCommerce team and other key stakeholders
Support the team with numerical / analytical and adhoc administrative project needs

 
These roles report to the Executive Manager - eCommerce.
 
COVID-19 update
At ALDI we believe that our employees should expect to come to work every day with the comfort and confidence that they are in the safest possible environment. You will be required to adhere to all ALDI and State and Federal Government COVID-safe practices and regulations.
From March 1st 2022, a condition of ongoing employment with ALDI will be that employees are fully vaccinated against COVID-19 unless they have a valid medical exemption. This requirement will apply to all employees across stores, warehouse, transport and offices.

Description: APRA is seeking a Principal Analyst to join our Authorised Deposit-taking Institutions (ADI) Strategic Insights team within the Data Analytics and Insights branch.  ADI Strategic Insights supports APRA's core functions and has responsibility for producing high quality analysis and reports relevant to the prudential supervision of the banking industry. The team utilise a range of data sources to develop insights and identify risks, including financial, economic and loan-level data. The team also contributes to the design of requirements for banks to report data to APRA.  As part of the team you will provide forward-looking analytics and insights, driving risk-based supervisory judgements and strategic decisions. The Principal Analyst plays a key role in shaping the delivery of data-driven insights and advice to APRA's senior executive, banking supervisors, risk specialists and other Government bodies.  You will work closely with senior specialists across APRA to identify emerging risks and formulate and prioritise key initiatives in response. You will also collaborate with a wide range of both APRA and industry stakeholders, and have an opportunity to lead significant projects that will impact the banking industry.  The successful candidate will have significant experience in the financial services industry, combined with a strong background in data analytics. You will have excellent problem-solving ability along with strong written and verbal communication skills. Experience with database queries and business intelligence tools is desirable. The team use SAS EG, R and Power BI, thus experience with these technologies is desirable but not essential.

You will be liaising with stakeholders at every level, daily, communication skills are of critical importance. You must technically astute and understand reporting, and specifically telephony reporting, as well as having the ability to work with scenario modelling. You should enjoy working in a team, this is a team focused environment. Although much of your role will be autonomous, communication and relationship building are key. You will join a warm and engaging environment, working as part of a driven team that align themselves to a core value of shared success.  They focus on assisting each other and working in cohesion. Description: As the Senior Resource Planning & Reporting Analyst, you will report to the Workforce Optimisation Manager. You will be responsible for short, medium, and long-term forecasting across any of the Channels within Customer and Business Operations (CBO) team of Bupa Health Insurance. Workload to be forecasted includes inbound and outbound calls, digital chat & messaging, e-mail, back-office transactions, retail demand and social interactions. You will be working very closely with Workforce Scheduling and Real Time Teams to produce short, medium, and long-term Service Level forecast & resource recommendations across assigned channels in CBO.  This is a Permanent Full-Time Opportunity and is based in Brisbane/Melbourne/Sydney when you're not working from home.  How will I help?  Key accountabilities include:  Deliver recommendations around resourcing in line with each team forward recruitment strategies ensuring that staffing requirements are balanced with the operating budget & are completed in conjunction with the appropriate stakeholder.Support stakeholders with the planning, management, and implementation of medium to long-term forecasts.Making recommendations using shrinkage targets to enable effective planning of activities. E.g. training, meetings, annual leave, and including tracking of turn over for recruitment.Provide detailed trend analysis of call volumes, Average Handle Time, shrinkage, Average Speed of Answer performance and other metrics as required, to improve forecasting accuracy and productivity.Identify areas for improvement in forecasting, scheduling, rostering and shift trade processes and make recommendations to take for implementation of these.Design, develop and maintain internal workforce management process and training documentation.Contribute to Continuous Improvement by analysing data and performing root cause analysis, identifying common process and procedure issues.What's in it for me?  As well as a competitive salary, a range of Bupa benefits and flexible working/ work from home arrangements, you'll be challenged and encouraged to innovate. You will collaborate strongly with colleagues who are committed to delivering exceptional experiences. We trust, respect and consider everyone, knowing your difference will make the difference.  What do I need?  Excellent understanding of Forecasting and Resource Planning processes and methodologyExperience in resource planning both Contact Centres (including Digital) & Back Office operation teamsWorking knowledge of Workforce Management Systems (Aspect eWFM experience desirable)Experience with the Aspect, Live Person and Genesys suite of products desirableAdvanced Excel & SAS skills highly desirableDemonstrated time management skills including the ability to manage competing priorities to achieve deadlines & desired outcomesWell-developed analytical and problem-solving skills, with proven ability to adopt a pro-active stance towards business issuesWhat is it like to work there?  Be at the heart of helping people live longer, healthier, happier lives. At Bupa, we employ more than 80,000 people globally who are making this a reality. One thing stands out about Bupa people -our customers are our passion; they're at the heart of our culture of care. If you've got the belief, the drive and the talent to help us in our ambition then we'd like to hear from you.

Key accountabilities include: Support the Delivery Hub Data and Insights Manager and Strategic Projects Manger to use data to discover insights, predict behaviour, through the visualisation and application of statistical and machine learning techniques with the ultimate objective of adding value to business decisionsEngage with business stakeholders, understand their pain-points, identify opportunities and contribute to developing analytical solutions that can create value for them, solving their most difficult problemsContribute to creating customer behaviour insights and risk assessment using advanced analytical techniques to support business decision making processes.Work within an agile framework to deliver incremental value to business customers through analytics projects or enhancements to existing AI solutionsSupport and champion a culture of innovation and analytical thinking across the businessWhat's in it for me?  As well as a competitive salary, a range of Bupa benefits and flexible working/ work from home arrangements, you'll be challenged and encouraged to innovate. You will collaborate strongly with colleagues who are committed to delivering exceptional experiences. We trust, respect, and consider everyone, knowing your difference will make the difference.  Perk highlights: Discount on our health insurance, travel, car, home, contents, and pet insurance products as well as Bupa services such as Dental and OpticalA 'People First' wellness program - SMILE. Provides a range of services such as health coaches, annual skin checks and flu vaccinations, assistance with nutrition, mental and general well-being guides, and product discounts. You will feel happier & healthier for working at Bupa!What do I need?  This is an exciting and changing time at Bupa. The role will suit an experienced senior analyst or senior data scientist with 5-7 years of experience who has good business acumen to work with stakeholders to identify and gain understanding of complex analytic questions. Ideally you will have gained experience in the Health Insurance or Insurance industries.  Key Skills and Experience required: Tertiary qualification in data science, statistics, mathematics, computer science, machine learning or similarFluency in SQL, Power BI and SASExperience using either R, Python or Scala programming languagesProficiency in other analytical tools such as Excel (VBA), SAS, GA360, Big Query and datasets such as Google Analytics and Adobe Analytics (preferred)Experience with technologies like AWS EMR to support ETL processing on large data sources or with computationally intensive steps (parallelization, Hadoop, Spark, etc.) (preferred)Strong communication and stakeholder management skills and the ability to communicate technical information to a non-technical audienceA passion to explore novel business questions and play a key role in a frank and lively dialogue with senior stakeholders to ask the better question and enable data driven insightsWhat is it like to work there?  Bupa is a world leading Health & Care organisation with over 22,000 people in Australia and New Zealand, and our purpose is to help people live longer, healthier, and happier lives. In Australia, we help to take care of people through our leading health insurance services as well as providing a personalised approach to care through our modern Dental clinic network, our Bupa Optical stores, Bupa Medical Visa services and over 70 Bupa Aged Care Homes. Bupa Therapy, along with our Medical and Wellbeing Centre provide a multidiscipline approach to care.  Our people reflect the diversity of our community. At Bupa, your wellbeing, identity and own story is respected and valued.

Description: Company DescriptionAbout SEEKSEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities.  We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.  Life at SEEKAt SEEK, innovation, creativity and passion drive us.  We challenge the status quo and retain the entrepreneurial spirit which drove our early success. This is what’s led us being named the AFR Boss Overall Winner for Best Place to Work in in Australasia, and the Best Place to Work – Technology.SEEK strives to support the wellbeing of our employees so they can lead more fulfilling and productive lives. Description:
A career that gives you more 
Your career at NAB is about more than money, it's about serving our customers well and helping our communities prosper. We currently have an opportunity for  a Consultant within the People Data and Analytics team.
 
The People Data & Analytics team supports the People Division and broader organisation with people data, reporting and analysis to enable fact-based decisions about our most valuable asset, our people.
This is an exciting and challenging role in the emerging field of people analytics and provides an excellent opportunity to advance your analytics skills in a collaborative and supportive team environment.
About you
To be successful in this role you will have:

A background working in data & analytics
The ability to communicate insights and new learnings to peers and stakeholders
Knowledge of data principles and methods to manage data sets
Experience utilising some of the following tools: SAP HR, Success Factors, Visier, Excel, Power BI, Service Now, or other HRIS & data visualisation tools.
High integrity, respecting highest standards of data privacy and data protection when dealing with sensitive, confidential, and personal information
An openness to new ways of thinking and working
Relevant tertiary qualifications

 
However, we don’t just look for someone based on their skills and expertise, we value a cultural fit and aptitude more than a shopping list of technical buzzwords. We value diversity in the team in the pursuit of excellence.  What we often look for in our team is:

Collaborative, creative, open to learning, a strong communicator.
Good relationship skills, and an ability to empathise with others.
Focus on simplicity and quality deliverables.
A passion for making a difference.

 
Day to day you will:
In this role you’ll contribute to insights for the People & Culture Domain and support transition to strategic state reporting. Ultimately you’ll ensure facts and evidence are used to supplement experience and intuition to drive more informed people decisions.
You’ll have the opportunity to lead and support a variety of deliverables and initiatives, including:

Creating and maintaining people metric scorecards and dashboards for the P&C Domain
Providing data and analysis support for key people initiatives and activities
Sourcing and transforming people data and creating integrated employee datasets
Working as part of multi-disciplinary squads to design, develop and deliver a range of people reporting products
Responding to ad hoc people questions and queries
Advising and enabling the ability to self-serve data sourcing and analysis
Engaging in knowledge sharing and contributing to the growth and success of the team

By joining NAB, you are committing to putting our customers’ needs first every time. You will be ambitious for growth; always curious and learning from colleagues. You will speak honestly, always valuing the time and opinion of others. You will own your work, doing what’s right, even when it’s hard.
NAB, invested in you 
We are committed to gender equality and are proud to be an equal opportunity employer and have a diverse and inclusive workforce. We have committed $70bn in financing to help address climate change and provide 2 days of paid leave each year through our employee volunteering program to support community organisations. 
We support our colleagues to be their best by offering a wide range of educational, financial, lifestyle, health & wellbeing benefits. For more information please visit here.  
Join NAB 
If you think this role is the right fit for you, we invite you to apply. Let’s explore who you are and what drives you. We’d love to share our vision for the future of banking.
To be eligible to apply, you must have Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency status. Please note candidate screening and interviews may be conducted prior to the closing date of the job advert.
*Please note unsolicited CVs from agencies will not be accepted.
To help keep our community safe, candidates are required to comply with vaccine requirements outlined in state based public health orders.

The Department of Jobs, Precincts and Regions (DJPR) was established to ensure Victoria's strong economic performance by growing industries and regions. Here at DJPR, we're making sure Victoria's economy benefits all Victorians by creating more jobs for more people, building thriving places and regions and nurturing inclusive communities.
The position of Data Analyst - DWH forms a part of the program centre within the Corporate Services and Delivery group.
The Program Centre supports the oversight and administration of grants and grant programs across DJPR. The Program Centre's aim is to drive continuous improvement in order to efficiently and effectively administer grant programs to deliver outcomes for the Victorian Government and the community.
The Program Centre provides advice on best practice grant program design, as well as implementation and grant administration services through a cost recovery model.
The Data Analyst works within the Program Centre which is responsible for leading centralised program design and systems integration for Department programs and initiatives that drive outcomes for key business, industry and community sectors across the Victorian economy.

Provide technical data analysis and modelling through the collection of information from GEMS/Oracle Datawarehouse and other relevant data sources and translate into reports appropriate for grant program management and analysis for stakeholders across the department.

Develop, schedule and update reports.

Actively contribute to the continuous improvement of business processes and systems.

About us:
About Alinta Energy:
At Alinta Energy, we’re constantly striving to do better. Whether it’s lowering customers costs, providing world class local service or sustainable energy, our aim is to be better. We support the development of renewable energy generation and offer local customer service through support hubs in Perth, Western Australia and Morwell in Victoria.

We are looking for an experienced Senior Analyst to join our dynamic Customer Operations team based in Melbourne. The primary role is to conduct analysis and deliver insights using internal/external data that will support strategic initiatives to manage Customer profitability and improve Customer Experience and Cash Flow outcomes.

Highly developed analytical and statistical skills

Hands on data analysis using ‘R’/Python/SQL/SAS

Utilities/Energy experience an advantage

Description: Company DescriptionAbout SEEKSEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities.  We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.Life at SEEKAt SEEK, innovation, creativity and passion drive us.  We challenge the status quo and retain the entrepreneurial spirit which drove our early success. This is what’s led us being named the AFR Boss Overall Winner for Best Place to Work in in Australasia, and the Best Place to Work – Technology.SEEK strives to support the wellbeing of our employees so they can lead more fulfilling and productive lives. We do this by providing our people with a phenomenal experience at work.  We support many types of flexible working arrangements and provide additional leave days such as personal flexi days and volunteer leave.Our state of the art offices in Cremorne provide an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues with our speciality spaces designed for testing, observation and research.  Internal wintergardens, along with outdoor terraces and courtyards provide areas to catch up with colleagues.  The Hub and Level 6 Terrace provide sweeping views of the city, as well as a games area featuring a pool table, table tennis table, Xbox Series X and PlayStation.The opportunities to collaborate and socialise with colleagues continue, with two hackathons a year and social events such as the SEEK Slam, SEEK Soccer, Footy and annual family carnival days.SEEK is also a proud sponsor of the Midsumma Festival and participates in loads of wellbeing programs throughout the year such as RuOKDay, Wellbeing week and many more.Job DescriptionAbout The TeamThe AI & Platform Services (AIPS) team exists within the Seek Group and provides AI-centric core services that scale globally including search, behavioural tracking, recommendations, candidate matching, ontological services, and personalisation.AIPS works primarily with internal partners, delivering services to these partners, who in turn deliver products to customers (candidates, hirers).Members of the AIPS team fall into one of three primary roles•    AI (artificial intelligence and machine learning)•    Strategy (business, product, go to market)•    Engineering (development, devops, operationalisation of models)People representing each of these roles are combined into squads which are in turn responsible for related sets of business services.About the SquadWe are looking for an engineer to join the Knowledge Graph squad. The Knowledge Graph squad consists of data scientists and engineers who work together to manage SEEK’s ontology assets and provide related services and solutions to the rest of the SEEK group. As an engineer you will be working with the ontologists to manage the ontology assets and serve the concepts in services then with the data scientists to continuously improve our production models, make new data sources available, optimise training pipelines, and ensuring the security and reliability of our systems.About The RoleThe Principal Engineer is a technical leader, their depth of experience and technical capacity drives outcomes for SEEK. The Principal Engineer works in / leads small teams to deliver fit-for-purpose, scalable, performant outcomes. The role is split between designing, hands-on work, and guiding others – and knowing when each element is important. Principal Engineers are responsible for one or more key SEEK systems – owning design, implementation and technical debt that align with the AIPS Technology Strategy and their Squad’s remit. The Principal Engineer works with their Engineering Manager to define system roadmaps, capacity planning, development processes. They take requirements and direction, and working with both their team, and other teams to determine how best to meet those needs. The Principal Engineer evangelises and communicates strong software development practice, interacting with their Squad, AIPS and the wider technical community to promote AIPS services, as well as to learn from others. Day to day tasks include:•    Leads the design and definition of software systems and components to meet your Squads remit, considering robustness, fault tolerance, scalability and performance.•    Being responsible for your service in production, its consistent uptime, troubleshooting, non-functional SLAs.•    Ensuring that systems are adequately developed, tested, and are fit for purpose.•    Collaborating closely with Data Scientists, Ontologists, Optimization Analysts, Data Services and Service and Strategy Managers to deliver excellent software for our partners in an agile environment.•    Working in a passionate, dynamic, growing environment with the ability to learn and adapt quickly to new methodologies and technologies.•    Driving towards continuous delivery; Act as an enabler for your team members, removing obstacles from their paths and identifying potentials for delivery, business and process improvements.•    Strive for technical excellence; Help communicate the healthy tension between the desire for immediate delivery and the long-term viability of the code base.•    Support experiments to assess performance of various algorithms and use the results to iteratively improve the platform.QualificationsAbout the Development EnvironmentThe team's services are using AWS and use a whole range of technologies like Fargate, lambdas, batch, ElastiCache built with Scala as well as some Python and Go. Description: Senior Data Analyst - NSW GovernmentLocation: Eveleigh, Sydney, with great WFH flexibilityRate: $700 - $780 per day + SuperContract Length: till 31/08/2022Note: Must have data and analytics experience focused on data driven and evidence based decision making.We are currently seeking an experienced Senior Data Analyst for our NSW Government client who will be responsible for using data and analytics to drive evidence based decision making, that informs the design of the market and the development of policies across the Vocational Education & Training (VET) sector and the wider Education and Skills Reform Division.Keys to Role:Role will suit an experienced Data Analyst who has experience in design and implementation of dataflows and data automation processes to support development of a single source of truth datawarehouse. Primary purpose of the role:A unique opportunity to embark on a career in data and analytics focused on data driven and evidence based decision making, to inform the design of the market and the development of policies across the Vocational Education & Training (VET) sector and the wider Education and Skills Reform Division.This role works hands-on in a number of high profile projects focused on initiatives to drive the design and management of the VET market framework to an outcomes and demand led approach. The team is in a unique position where it has significant control of the end-to-end data and analytics infrastructure stack, and with endless opportunities only limited to technical capabilities of the team.Key accountabilities:* Delivery of business analytics, business intelligence and ad-hoc analysis.* Design and implementation of dataflows and data automation processes to support development of a single source of truth datawarehouse. This includes the building, updating and amending of tables, views and datamarts, taking into account both back-end organisation and front-end accessibility for end users (technical and non-technical).* Automation and scheduling of data management and data quality processes, ensuring appropriate data dictionaries and documentation to transition to other staff members into business as usual. This includes development of data standards, procedures and definitions.* Change management and impact assessment of data quality and provision from upstream systems changes and other projects initiated from within the team. * Actively identify and implement improvements to the sourcing and accuracy of data.* Identify sourcing and integration new potential external data sources.Key challenges:* Delivering sophisticated analysis and projects to the required standards and timeframes, given the need to rapidly understand and integrate information and adapt in an often changing and unpredictable environment* Providing clear analytical advice using multiple sources of data within tight timeframes.
